33const char *
34target_name(DTYPE dtype)
35{
36 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
37 switch (ty) {
38 case TY_DCMPLX:
39 if (XBIT(57, 0x200)) {
40 return "complex*16";
41 }
42 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
43 case TY_LOG:
44 case TY_INT:
45 case TY_FLOAT:
46 case TY_SLOG:
47 case TY_SINT:
48 case TY_BINT:
49 case TY_BLOG:
50 case TY_DBLE:
51 case TY_QUAD:
52 case TY_CMPLX:
53 case TY_QCMPLX:
54 case TY_INT8:
55 case TY_LOG8:
56 case TY_CHAR:
57 case TY_NCHAR:
58 return dtypeinfo[ty].target_type;
59
60 default:
61 interr("target_name: bad dtype ", ty, 3);
62 return "";
63 }
64}

95ISZ_T
96size_of(DTYPE dtype)
97{
98 ISZ_T d, nelems, sz;
99 INT clen;
100 ADSC *ad;
101
102 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
103 switch (ty) {
104 case TY_WORD:
105 case TY_DWORD:
106 case TY_LOG:
107 case TY_INT:
108 case TY_FLOAT:
109 case TY_PTR:
110 case TY_SLOG:
111 case TY_SINT:
112 case TY_BINT:
113 case TY_BLOG:
114 case TY_DBLE:
115 case TY_QUAD:
116 case TY_CMPLX:
117 case TY_DCMPLX:
118 case TY_QCMPLX:
119 case TY_INT8:
120 case TY_LOG8:
121 return dtypeinfo[ty].size;
122
123 case TY_HOLL:
124 /* treat like default integer type */
125 return dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_INT)].size;
126
127 case TY_CHAR:
128 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR)
129 interr("size_of: attempt to get size of assumed size character", 0, 3);
130 clen = string_length(dtype);
131 return clen;
132
133 case TY_NCHAR:
134 if (dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR)
135 interr("size_of: attempt to get size of assumed size ncharacter", 0, 3);
136 clen = string_length(dtype);
137 return 2 * clen;
138
139 case TY_ARRAY:
140 if ((d = DTY(dtype + 2)) <= 0) {
141 interr("size_of: no array descriptor", (int)d, 3);
142 return size_of((int)DTY(dtype + 1));
143 }
144 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
145 if (AD_DEFER(ad)) {
146 return dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_PTR)].size;
147 }
148 if (AD_NUMELM(ad) == 0) {
149/* illegal use of adjustable or assumed-size array:
150 should have been caught in semant. */
151/* errsev(50); */
152 if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
153 AD_NUMELM(ad) = astb.k1;
154 d = stb.i1;
155 } else {
156 AD_NUMELM(ad) = astb.i1;
157 d = stb.i1;
158 }
159 } else {
160 switch (A_TYPEG(AD_NUMELM(ad))) {
161 case A_BINOP:
162 case A_UNOP:
163 /* FS#20474: Occurs with length type parameters. Treat as
164 * as if AD_DEFER(ad) is set (see case above).
165 * This also avoids an ICE from call to sym_of_ast() below.
166 */
167 return dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_PTR)].size;
168 }
169 d = AD_NUMELM(ad);
170 if (A_TYPEG(d) == A_INTR) {
171 switch (A_OPTYPEG(d)) {
172 case I_INT1:
173 case I_INT2:
174 case I_INT4:
175 case I_INT8:
176 case I_INT:
177 /* FS#22205: This can occur with -mcmodel=medium */
178 d = A_ARGSG(d);
179 break;
180 default:
181 interr("size_of: unexpected intrinsic optype ", A_OPTYPEG(d), 3);
182 }
183 }
184 d = sym_of_ast(d);
185 if (d == stb.i0 || STYPEG(d) != ST_CONST) {
186 /* illegal use of adjustable or assumed-size array:
187 should have been caught in semant. */
188 /* errsev(50); */
189 AD_NUMELM(ad) = astb.i1;
190 d = stb.i1;
191 }
192 if (XBIT(68, 0x1) && d == stb.k0) {
193 AD_NUMELM(ad) = astb.k1;
194 d = stb.k1;
195 }
196 }
197 if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
198 INT num[2];
199 num[0] = CONVAL1G(d);
200 num[1] = CONVAL2G(d);
201 INT64_2_ISZ(num, d);
202 } else
203 d = CONVAL2G(d);
204 nelems = d;
205 sz = size_of((int)DTY(dtype + 1));
206 d = d * sz;
207 if (size_sym && (d < nelems || d < sz) && nelems && sz) {
208 return -1;
209 }
210 return d;
211
212 case TY_STRUCT:
213 case TY_UNION:
214 case TY_DERIVED:
215 if (DTY(dtype + 1) == 0) {
216 errsev(151);
217 return 4;
218 } else
219 return DTY(dtype + 2);
220
221 default:
222 interr("size_of: bad dtype ", ty, 3);
223 return 1;
224 }
225}

227/** \brief Return length of constant char string data type */
228int
229string_length(DTYPE dtype)
230{
231 int clen;
232 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
233 case TY_CHAR:
234 case TY_NCHAR:
235 break;
236 default:
237 interr("string length applied to nonstring datatype", dtype, 2);
238 return 1;
239 }
240 clen = DTY(dtype + 1); /* get length ast */
241 clen = A_ALIASG(clen); /* get constant alias */
242 clen = A_SPTRG(clen); /* get constant symbol */
243 clen = CONVAL2G(clen); /* get constant value */
244 if (clen < 0)
245 return 0;
246 return clen;
247}

249/*
250 * A framework for recursively scanning derived types and their members
251 * with pluggable predicates follows. The results are not cached,
252 * but probably could be. This code is used below to replace a series
253 * of functions that used boilerplate to implement their own variant
254 * frameworks.
255 */
256
257/* Visitation lists record the datatypes that have been visited and
258 * whether those visits remain active.
259 */
260struct visit_list {
261 DTYPE dtype;
262 LOGICAL is_active;
263 struct visit_list *next;
264};
265
266static struct visit_list *
267visit_list_scan(struct visit_list *list, DTYPE dtype)
268{
269 for (; list; list = list->next) {
270 if (list->dtype == dtype)
271 break;
272 }
273 return list;
274}
275
276static void
277visit_list_push(struct visit_list **list, DTYPE dtype)
278{
279 struct visit_list *newlist;
280 NEW(newlist, struct visit_list, 1);
281 newlist->dtype = dtype;
282 newlist->is_active = TRUE;
283 newlist->next = *list;
284 *list = newlist;
285}
286
287static void
288visit_list_free(struct visit_list **list)
289{
290 struct visit_list *p;
291 while ((p = *list)) {
292 *list = p->next;
293 FREE(p);
294 }
295}

297static LOGICAL
298is_container_dtype(DTYPE dtype)
299{
300 if (dtype > 0) {
301 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
302 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
303 switch (DTYG(dtype)) {
304 case TY_DERIVED:
305 case TY_STRUCT:
306 case TY_UNION:
307 return TRUE;
308 }
309 }
310 return FALSE;
311}
312
313/* Forward declare is_recursive() here so that search_type_members()
314 * below can identify it as a special case.
315 */
316static LOGICAL is_recursive(int sptr, struct visit_list **visited);
317
318typedef LOGICAL (*stm_predicate_t)(int member_sptr,
319 struct visit_list **visited);
320
321/* search_type_members() is a potentially recursive scanner of
322 * derived types that applies a given predicate function against the
323 * component members. Returns TRUE if any application of the predicate
324 * is satisfied. The predicate function can (and usually does) indirectly
325 * recursively call search_type_members() to scan the types of
326 * members, but it has the option to recurse conditionally or not at all.
327 */
328static LOGICAL
329search_type_members(DTYPE dtype, stm_predicate_t predicate,
330 struct visit_list **visited)
331{
332 LOGICAL result = FALSE;
333
334 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
335 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
336 if (is_container_dtype(dtype)) {
337 int member_sptr = DTY(dtype + 1);
338 struct visit_list *active = visit_list_scan(*visited, dtype);
339
340 if (active) {
341 /* This dtype has already been scanned or is in process.
342 * Cut off the scan, and return FALSE unless the search
343 * is for recursive types and we've just found one.
344 */
345 return predicate == is_recursive && active->is_active;
346 }
347
348 visit_list_push(visited, dtype);
349 active = *visited;
350
351 /* Traverse the members of the derived type. */
352 while (member_sptr > NOSYM && !(result = predicate(member_sptr, visited))) {
353 member_sptr = SYMLKG(member_sptr);
354 }
355
356 /* The scan of this data type is complete. Leave it on the visited
357 * list to forestall another failed pass later.
358 */
359 active->is_active = FALSE;
360 }
361 return result;
362}
363
364/* Wraps a call to search_type_members() above with the construction
365 * and destruction of its visitation list.
366 */
367static LOGICAL
368search_type_members_wrapped(DTYPE dtype, stm_predicate_t predicate)
369{
370 struct visit_list *visited = NULL;
371 LOGICAL result = search_type_members(dtype, predicate, &visited);
372 visit_list_free(&visited);
373 return result;
374}
375
376/* Driver for predicates that use search_type_members(); it sets up and
377 * tears down the visitation list that search_type_members() uses.
378 * N.B. this function will succeed if the supplied predicate is true on
379 * the initial symbol table index, even if it's not a component.
380 */
381static LOGICAL
382test_sym_and_components(int sptr, stm_predicate_t predicate)
383{
384 struct visit_list *visited = NULL;
385 LOGICAL result = predicate(sptr, &visited);
386 visit_list_free(&visited);
387 return result;
388}
389
390static LOGICAL
391test_sym_components_only(int sptr, stm_predicate_t predicate)
392{
393 return sptr > NOSYM && search_type_members_wrapped(DTYPEG(sptr), predicate);
394}

396/** \brief Check for special case of empty typedef which has a size of 0
397 but one member of type DT_NONE to indicate that the type is
398 empty and not incomplete, a forward reference, etc.
399 */
400LOGICAL
401is_empty_typedef(DTYPE dtype)
402{
403 SPTR sptr;
404 if (dtype) {
405 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
406 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
407 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
408 case TY_DERIVED:
409 case TY_UNION:
410 case TY_STRUCT:
411 for (sptr = DTY(dtype + 1); sptr > NOSYM;
412 sptr = SYMLKG(sptr)) {
413 /* Type parameters are not data components. Skip type parameters. */
414 if (SETKINDG(sptr) || LENPARMG(sptr)) {
415 continue;
416 }
417 return FALSE;
418 }
419 return TRUE;
420 }
421 }
422 return FALSE;
423}
424
425/** \brief Check for special case of zero-size typedef which may nest have
426 zero-size typedef compnents or zero-size array compnents.
427 */
428LOGICAL
429is_zero_size_typedef(DTYPE dtype)
430{
431 if (dtype <= DT_NONE)
432 return FALSE;
433 dtype = is_array_dtype(dtype) ? DTY(dtype + 1) : dtype;
434
435 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
436 case TY_DERIVED:
437 case TY_UNION:
438 case TY_STRUCT:
439 return (DTY(dtype + 2) == 0);
440 default:
441 return FALSE;
442 }
443 return FALSE;
444}

446static LOGICAL
447is_recursive_dtype(int sptr, struct visit_list **visited)
448{
449 return sptr > NOSYM &&
450 search_type_members(sptr, is_recursive_dtype, visited);
451}

453/* N.B., no_data_components_recursive() will only ever be true for
454 * data types that are containers, so types like INTEGER will map to FALSE.
455 */
456static bool
457no_data_components_recursive(DTYPE dtype, stm_predicate_t predicate, struct visit_list **visited)
458{
459 /* For the derived type in dtype: Returns true if dtype is empty or
460 * if it does not contain any data components (i.e., a derived type with
461 * type bound procedures returns false). Otherwise, returns false.
462 */
463 int mem_sptr;
464 struct visit_list *active;
465 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
466 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
467 active = visit_list_scan(*visited, dtype);
468 if (is_empty_typedef(dtype))
469 return TRUE;
470 if (!is_container_dtype(dtype))
471 return FALSE;
472 if (active) {
473 /* This dtype has already been scanned or is in process.
474 * Cut off the scan, and return FALSE unless the search
475 * is for recursive types and we've just found one.
476 */
477 return predicate == is_recursive_dtype && active->is_active;
478 }
479
480 visit_list_push(visited, dtype);
481 active = *visited;
482
483 for (mem_sptr = DTY(dtype + 1); mem_sptr > NOSYM;
484 mem_sptr = SYMLKG(mem_sptr)) {
485 if (DTYG(DTYPEG(mem_sptr)) == TY_DERIVED) {
486 if (!no_data_components_recursive(DTYPEG(mem_sptr), is_recursive_dtype, visited)) {
487 active->is_active = FALSE;
488 return FALSE;
489 }
490 } else if (!CLASSG(mem_sptr) || !BINDG(mem_sptr) || !VTABLEG(mem_sptr)) {
491 active->is_active = FALSE;
492 return FALSE;
493 }
494 }
495 return TRUE;
496}
497
498/* Wrapper to no_data_components_recursive() to detect cycles. */
499LOGICAL
500no_data_components(DTYPE dtype)
501{
502 struct visit_list *visited = NULL;
503 LOGICAL result = no_data_components_recursive(dtype, is_recursive_dtype, &visited);
504 visit_list_free(&visited);
505 return result;
506}

508/** \brief Return the size of this variable, taking into account
509 such things like whether the variable is a pointer */
510ISZ_T
511size_of_var(int sptr)
512{
513 DTYPE dtype;
514 ISZ_T sz;
515
516 if (is_tbp_or_final(sptr)) {
517 return 0; /* type bound procedure */
518 }
519 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
520
521 if (POINTERG(sptr) || ALLOCG(sptr)) {
522 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
523 /* array pointer, size of pointer+offset+descriptor */
524 /* pointer is a pointer, offset and descriptor are DT_INT */
525 int rank = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
526 int descsize = get_descriptor_len(rank);
527 return dtypeinfo[TY_PTR].size +
528 (descsize + 1) * dtypeinfo[DTY(stb.dt_int)].size;
529 }
530 /* scalar pointer, size of pointer */
531 return dtypeinfo[TY_PTR].size;
532 }
533 /* not a pointer, just return the size of the type of the variable */
534 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PLIST) {
535 sz = PLLENG(sptr) * size_of(dtype);
536 return sz;
537 }
538
539 /* normal size of */
540 size_sym = sptr;
541 sz = size_of(dtype);
542 if (sz < 0) {
543 error(219, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), NULL);
544 sz = 1;
545 }
546 size_sym = 0;
547 return sz;
548} /* size_of_var */
549
550INT
551size_ast(int sptr, DTYPE dtype)
552{
553 INT d, len, clen, mlpyr = 1;
554 ISZ_T val1;
555 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
556
557 switch (ty) {
558 case TY_WORD:
559 case TY_DWORD:
560 case TY_LOG:
561 case TY_INT:
562 case TY_FLOAT:
563 case TY_PTR:
564 case TY_SLOG:
565 case TY_SINT:
566 case TY_BINT:
567 case TY_BLOG:
568 case TY_DBLE:
569 case TY_QUAD:
570 case TY_CMPLX:
571 case TY_DCMPLX:
572 case TY_QCMPLX:
573 case TY_INT8:
574 case TY_LOG8:
575 return mk_isz_cval(dtypeinfo[ty].size, astb.bnd.dtype);
576
577 case TY_HOLL:
578 /* treat like default integer type */
579 return mk_isz_cval(dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_INT)].size, astb.bnd.dtype);
580
581 case TY_NCHAR:
582 mlpyr = 2;
583 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
584 case TY_CHAR:
585 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR
586 || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR
587 ) {
588 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR
589 || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR
590 ) {
591 clen = ast_intr(I_LEN, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, mk_id(sptr));
592 } else {
593 clen = DTY(dtype+1);
594 }
595 } else if (ADJLENG(sptr) && !F90POINTERG(sptr)) {
596 /* don't add CVLEN for local automatic character */
597 clen = CVLENG(sptr);
598 if (clen == 0) {
599 clen = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptr), "len", astb.bnd.dtype);
600 CVLENP(sptr, clen);
601 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
602 CCSYMP(clen, 1);
603 }
604 clen = mk_id(clen);
605 } else {
606 clen = DTY(dtype + 1);
607 if (A_ALIASG(clen)) {
608 clen = A_ALIASG(clen);
609 clen = A_SPTRG(clen);
610 clen = CONVAL2G(clen);
611 return mk_isz_cval(mlpyr * clen, astb.bnd.dtype);
612 }
613 clen = mk_convert(clen, astb.bnd.dtype);
614 }
615 if (mlpyr != 1) {
616 len = mk_isz_cval(mlpyr, astb.bnd.dtype);
617 clen = mk_binop(OP_MUL, len, clen, astb.bnd.dtype);
618 }
619 return clen;
620
621 case TY_ARRAY:
622 len = size_ast(sptr, DTY(dtype + 1));
623 if (DTY(dtype + 2) <= 0) {
624 interr("size_ast: no array descriptor", dtype, 3);
625 return len;
626 }
627 if (ADD_DEFER(dtype)) {
628 return mk_isz_cval(dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_PTR)].size, astb.bnd.dtype);
629 }
630 if (ADD_NUMELM(dtype) == 0) {
631 /* illegal use of adjustable or assumed-size array:
632 should have been caught in semant. */
633 /* errsev(50); */
634 ADD_NUMELM(dtype) = astb.bnd.one;
635 d = stb.i1;
636 } else {
637 d = sym_of_ast(ADD_NUMELM(dtype));
638 if (d == stb.i0 || STYPEG(d) != ST_CONST) {
639 /* illegal use of adjustable or assumed-size array:
640 should have been caught in semant. */
641 /* errsev(50); */
642 ADD_NUMELM(dtype) = astb.bnd.one;
643 d = stb.i1;
644 }
645 }
646 val1 = ad_val_of(d);
647 if (A_TYPEG(len) == A_CNST) {
648 int dd;
649 ISZ_T val2;
650
651 dd = sym_of_ast(len);
652 if (STYPEG(dd) != ST_CONST) {
653 dd = stb.i1;
654 }
655 val2 = ad_val_of(dd);
656 return mk_isz_cval(val1 * val2, astb.bnd.dtype);
657 }
658 d = mk_cval(val1, astb.bnd.dtype);
659 return mk_binop(OP_MUL, d, len, astb.bnd.dtype);
660
661 case TY_STRUCT:
662 case TY_UNION:
663 case TY_DERIVED:
664 if (DTY(dtype + 2) <= 0 && (!CLASSG(sptr) || !DTY(dtype + 1)) &&
665 !has_tbp_or_final(dtype) && !UNLPOLYG(DTY(dtype + 3))) {
666 return mk_isz_cval(4, astb.bnd.dtype);
667 } else {
668 return mk_isz_cval(DTY(dtype + 2), astb.bnd.dtype);
669 }
670
671 default:
672 interr("size_ast: bad dtype", ty, 3);
673 return mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
674 }
675}

677/** \brief Like size_ast(), but pass an AST, allowing for member references */
678INT
679size_ast_of(int ast, DTYPE dtype)
680{
681 INT d, len, clen, mlpyr = 1, sptr = 0, concat;
682 ISZ_T val;
683 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
684
685 switch (ty) {
686 case TY_WORD:
687 case TY_DWORD:
688 case TY_LOG:
689 case TY_INT:
690 case TY_FLOAT:
691 case TY_PTR:
692 case TY_SLOG:
693 case TY_SINT:
694 case TY_BINT:
695 case TY_BLOG:
696 case TY_DBLE:
697 case TY_QUAD:
698 case TY_CMPLX:
699 case TY_DCMPLX:
700 case TY_QCMPLX:
701 case TY_INT8:
702 case TY_LOG8:
703 return mk_isz_cval(dtypeinfo[ty].size, astb.bnd.dtype);
704
705 case TY_HOLL:
706 /* treat like default integer type */
707 return mk_isz_cval(dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_INT)].size, astb.bnd.dtype);
708
709 case TY_NCHAR:
710 mlpyr = 2;
711 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
712 case TY_CHAR:
713 concat = 0;
714 if (ast) {
715 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSTR)
716 ast = A_LOPG(ast);
717 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR)
718 ast = A_LOPG(ast);
719 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_FUNC)
720 ast = A_LOPG(ast);
721 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_CNST) {
722 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
723 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID) {
724 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
725 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM) {
726 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast));
727 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_BINOP && A_OPTYPEG(ast) == OP_CAT) {
728 sptr = 0;
729 concat = 1;
730 } else {
731 interr("size_ast_of: unexpected ast type", A_TYPEG(ast), 3);
732 sptr = 0;
733 }
734 } else {
735 sptr = 0;
736 }
737 if (sptr && (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR
738 || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR
739 )) {
740 clen = ast_intr(I_LEN, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, ast);
741 } else if (sptr && ADJLENG(sptr) && !F90POINTERG(sptr)) {
742 /* don't add CVLEN for local automatic character */
743 clen = CVLENG(sptr);
744 if (clen == 0) {
745 clen = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptr), "len", astb.bnd.dtype);
746 CVLENP(sptr, clen);
747 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
748 CCSYMP(clen, 1);
749 }
750 clen = mk_id(clen);
751 } else {
752 clen = DTY(dtype + 1);
753 if (clen == 0 && concat) {
754 /* get the length of the concatenation operands */
755 int lsize, rsize;
756 lsize = size_ast_of(A_LOPG(ast), A_DTYPEG(A_LOPG(ast)));
757 rsize = size_ast_of(A_ROPG(ast), A_DTYPEG(A_ROPG(ast)));
758 return mk_binop(OP_ADD, lsize, rsize, astb.bnd.dtype);
759 }
760 if (A_ALIASG(clen)) {
761 clen = A_ALIASG(clen);
762 clen = A_SPTRG(clen);
763 clen = CONVAL2G(clen);
764 return mk_isz_cval(mlpyr * clen, astb.bnd.dtype);
765 }
766 clen = mk_convert(clen, astb.bnd.dtype);
767 clen =
768 ast_intr(I_MAX, astb.bnd.dtype, 2, clen, mk_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype));
769 }
770 if (mlpyr != 1) {
771 len = mk_cval(mlpyr, astb.bnd.dtype);
772 clen = mk_binop(OP_MUL, len, clen, astb.bnd.dtype);
773 }
774 return clen;
775
776 case TY_ARRAY:
777 len = size_ast_of(ast, DTY(dtype + 1));
778 if (DTY(dtype + 2) <= 0) {
779 interr("size_ast_of: no array descriptor", dtype, 3);
780 return len;
781 }
782 if (ADD_DEFER(dtype)) {
783 return mk_cval(dtypeinfo[DTY(DT_PTR)].size, DT_INT);
784 }
785 if (ADD_NUMELM(dtype) == 0) {
786 /* illegal use of adjustable or assumed-size array:
787 should have been caught in semant. */
788 /* errsev(50); */
789 ADD_NUMELM(dtype) = astb.bnd.one;
790 d = stb.i1;
791 } else {
792 d = sym_of_ast(ADD_NUMELM(dtype));
793 if (d == stb.i0 || STYPEG(d) != ST_CONST) {
794 /* illegal use of adjustable or assumed-size array:
795 should have been caught in semant. */
796 /* errsev(50); */
797 ADD_NUMELM(dtype) = astb.bnd.one;
798 d = stb.i1;
799 }
800 }
801 val = ad_val_of(d);
802 if (A_TYPEG(len) == A_CNST) {
803 int dd;
804 ISZ_T val2;
805 dd = sym_of_ast(len);
806 if (STYPEG(dd) != ST_CONST) {
807 dd = stb.i1;
808 }
809 val2 = ad_val_of(dd);
810 return mk_isz_cval(val * val2, astb.bnd.dtype);
811 }
812 d = mk_isz_cval(d, astb.bnd.dtype);
813 return mk_binop(OP_MUL, d, len, astb.bnd.dtype);
814
815 case TY_STRUCT:
816 case TY_UNION:
817 case TY_DERIVED:
818 if (!sptr)
819 sptr = DTY(dtype + 1);
820 if (DTY(dtype + 2) <= 0 && !UNLPOLYG(DTY(dtype+3)) &&
821 (!CLASSG(sptr) || !DTY(dtype + 1))) {
822 errsev(151);
823 return mk_isz_cval(4, astb.bnd.dtype);
824 } else {
825 return mk_isz_cval(DTY(dtype + 2), astb.bnd.dtype);
826 }
827
828 default:
829 interr("size_ast_of: bad dtype", ty, 3);
830 return mk_isz_cval(1, astb.bnd.dtype);
831 }
832} /* size_ast_of */
833
834INT
835string_expr_length(int ast)
836{
837 int len, al, ar;
838 DTYPE dt_int;
839 int sym, iface;
840 /* must be constant reference, symbol reference, or concatenation */
841 if (ast <= 0)
842 return astb.i0;
843 dt_int = DT_INT;
844 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
845 case A_ID:
846 case A_CNST:
847 case A_MEM:
848 return size_ast_of(ast, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast)));
849 case A_SUBSTR:
850 if (A_DTYPEG(A_LEFTG(ast)) == DT_INT8)
851 dt_int = DT_INT8;
852 else if (A_DTYPEG(A_RIGHTG(ast)) == DT_INT8)
853 dt_int = DT_INT8;
854 if (A_RIGHTG(ast)) {
855 if (A_LEFTG(ast) == 0) {
856 len = A_RIGHTG(ast);
857 } else {
858 int l1;
859 l1 = mk_binop(OP_SUB, A_LEFTG(ast), astb.i1, dt_int);
860 len = mk_binop(OP_SUB, A_RIGHTG(ast), l1, dt_int);
861 }
862 } else {
863 if (A_LEFTG(ast) == 0) {
864 return string_expr_length(A_LOPG(ast));
865 } else {
866 int l1, l2;
867 l1 = mk_binop(OP_SUB, A_LEFTG(ast), astb.i1, dt_int);
868 l2 = string_expr_length(A_LOPG(ast));
869 len = mk_binop(OP_SUB, l2, l1, dt_int);
870 }
871 }
872 if (A_ALIASG(len)) {
873 int cvlen;
874 cvlen = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(len));
875 if (cvlen < 0)
876 len = mk_cval(0, DT_INT4);
877 } else if (dt_int != DT_INT8)
878 len = ast_intr(I_MAX, DT_INT4, 2, len, mk_cval(0, DT_INT4));
879 else
880 len = ast_intr(I_MAX, DT_INT8, 2, len, mk_cval(0, DT_INT8));
881 return len;
882 case A_SUBSCR:
883 /* subscripted reference, just get the length of the symbol */
884 return string_expr_length(A_LOPG(ast));
885 case A_PAREN:
886 case A_CONV:
887 return string_expr_length(A_LOPG(ast));
888 case A_BINOP:
889 if (A_OPTYPEG(ast) != OP_CAT) {
890 interr("string_expr_length: operator not concatenation", A_OPTYPEG(ast),
891 3);
892 return astb.i0;
893 }
894 al = string_expr_length(A_LOPG(ast));
895 ar = string_expr_length(A_ROPG(ast));
896 if (A_DTYPEG(al) == DT_INT8)
897 dt_int = DT_INT8;
898 else if (A_DTYPEG(ar) == DT_INT8)
899 dt_int = DT_INT8;
900 len = mk_binop(OP_ADD, al, ar, dt_int);
901 return ast_intr(I_MAX, dt_int, 2, len, mk_cval(0, dt_int));
902 case A_FUNC:
903 /* FS#21600: need to get the interface from the A_FUNC ast. */
904 sym = procsym_of_ast(A_LOPG(ast));
905 iface = 0;
906 proc_arginfo(sym, NULL, NULL, &iface);
907 return string_expr_length(mk_id(iface));
908 case A_INTR:
909 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
910 case I_TRIM:
911 return ast_intr(I_LEN_TRIM, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(ast), 0));
912 case I_RESHAPE:
913 return ast_intr(I_LEN, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(ast), 0));
914 case I_ACHAR:
915 case I_CHAR:
916 return ast_intr(I_INT, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(ast), 0));
917 }
918 /* else fall thru */
919 default:
920 interr("string_expr_length: ast not string op", A_TYPEG(ast), 3);
921 return astb.i0;
922 }
923} /* string_expr_length */

925/** \brief Change \p dtype from assumed-length to length of \p ast */
926DTYPE
927adjust_ch_length(DTYPE dtype, int ast)
928{
929 int len;
930 /* if 'dtype' is assumed-length character, create a new
931 * datatype with same character type, but with length equal
932 * to length of the expression ast 'ast' */
933 dtype = DDTG(dtype);
934 if (dtype != DT_ASSNCHAR && dtype != DT_ASSCHAR && dtype != DT_DEFERNCHAR &&
935 dtype != DT_DEFERCHAR) {
936 return dtype;
937 }
938 len = string_expr_length(ast);
939 if (len) {
940 dtype = get_type(2, DTY(dtype), len);
941 }
942 return dtype;
943} /* adjust_ch_length */
944
945/** \brief Fix array and char dtypes.
946
947 Given datatype \p dtype and symbol \p sptr, return a datatype
948 equivalent to the given datatype, but with any array bounds
949 filled in from the symbol's array bounds, and char length
950 filled in from the symbol's char length, using
951 calls to LBOUND, UBOUND, or LEN, as necessary.
952 */
953DTYPE
954fix_dtype(int sptr, DTYPE dtype)
955{
956 DTYPE elemdt;
957 int sym;
958 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
959
960 if (sptr <= NOSYM)
961 return dtype;
962
963 switch (ty) {
964 case TY_WORD:
965 case TY_DWORD:
966 case TY_LOG:
967 case TY_INT:
968 case TY_FLOAT:
969 case TY_PTR:
970 case TY_SLOG:
971 case TY_SINT:
972 case TY_BINT:
973 case TY_BLOG:
974 case TY_DBLE:
975 case TY_QUAD:
976 case TY_CMPLX:
977 case TY_DCMPLX:
978 case TY_QCMPLX:
979 case TY_INT8:
980 case TY_LOG8:
981 case TY_HOLL:
982 case TY_STRUCT:
983 case TY_UNION:
984 case TY_DERIVED:
985 return dtype;
986
987 case TY_NCHAR:
988 case TY_CHAR:
989 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR
990 || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR
991 ) {
992 int clen = ast_intr(I_LEN, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, mk_id(sptr));
993 return get_type(2, ty, clen);
994 }
995 if (ADJLENG(sptr) && !F90POINTERG(sptr)) {
996 /* don't add CVLEN for local automatic character */
997 int cvlen;
998 int clen = CVLENG(sptr);
999 if (clen == 0) {
1000 clen = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptr), "len", DT_INT);
1001 CVLENP(sptr, clen);
1002 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
1003 CCSYMP(clen, 1);
1004 }
1005 cvlen = CVLENG(sptr);
1006 clen = mk_id(clen);
1007 clen = ast_intr(I_MAX, DTYPEG(cvlen), 2, clen, mk_cval(0, DTYPEG(cvlen)));
1008 return get_type(2, ty, clen);
1009 }
1010 return dtype;
1011
1012 case TY_ARRAY:
1013 if (DTY(dtype + 2) <= 0) {
1014 interr("fix_dtype: no array descriptor", dtype, 3);
1015 return dtype;
1016 }
1017 elemdt = fix_dtype(sptr, DTY(dtype + 1));
1018 sym = mk_id(sptr);
1019 if (ADD_ASSUMSHP(dtype) == 1) {
1020 /* get bounds from that of sptr */
1021 int ndim = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
1022 DTYPE dt = get_array_dtype(ndim, elemdt);
1023 int i;
1024 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
1025 int up, ext;
1026 ADD_MLPYR(dt, i) = 0;
1027 ADD_LWBD(dt, i) = ADD_LWBD(dtype, i);
1028 ADD_LWAST(dt, i) = ADD_LWAST(dtype, i);
1029 up = ADD_UPBD(dtype, i);
1030 if (up == 0) {
1031 up = ast_intr(I_UBOUND, DT_INT, 2, sym, i + 1);
1032 ADD_UPBD(dt, i) = up;
1033 ADD_UPAST(dt, i) = up;
1034 } else {
1035 ADD_UPBD(dt, i) = ADD_UPBD(dtype, i);
1036 ADD_UPAST(dt, i) = ADD_UPAST(dtype, i);
1037 }
1038 ext = mk_extent(ADD_LWAST(dt, i), ADD_UPAST(dtype, i), i);
1039 ADD_EXTNTAST(dt, i) = ext;
1040 }
1041 ADD_NUMELM(dt) = 0;
1042 ADD_ZBASE(dt) = 0;
1043 return dt;
1044 }
1045 if (elemdt != DTY(dtype + 1)) {
1046 /* same array bounds, different subtype */
1047 int ndim = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
1048 DTYPE dt = get_array_dtype(ndim, elemdt);
1049 int i;
1050 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
1051 ADD_MLPYR(dt, i) = ADD_MLPYR(dtype, i);
1052 ADD_LWBD(dt, i) = ADD_LWBD(dtype, i);
1053 ADD_UPBD(dt, i) = ADD_UPBD(dtype, i);
1054 ADD_LWAST(dt, i) = ADD_LWAST(dtype, i);
1055 ADD_UPAST(dt, i) = ADD_UPAST(dtype, i);
1056 ADD_EXTNTAST(dt, i) = ADD_EXTNTAST(dtype, i);
1057 }
1058 ADD_NUMELM(dt) = ADD_NUMELM(dtype);
1059 ADD_ZBASE(dt) = ADD_ZBASE(dtype);
1060 return dt;
1061 }
1062 return dtype;
1063
1064 default:
1065 interr("fix_dtype: bad dtype", dtype * 1000 + ty, 3);
1066 return dtype;
1067 }
1068} /* fix_dtype */

1070ISZ_T
1071extent_of(DTYPE dtype)
1072{
1073 ISZ_T d;
1074 ADSC *ad;
1075 int numelem;
1076
1077#if DEBUG
1078 assert(DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY, "extent_of, expected TY_ARRAY", dtype, 3);
1079#endif
1080 if ((d = DTY(dtype + 2)) <= 0) {
1081 interr("extent_of: no array descriptor", (int)d, 3);
1082 return 0;
1083 }
1084 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
1085 numelem = AD_NUMELM(ad);
1086 if (numelem == 0)
1087 return 0;
1088 if (A_ALIASG(numelem) == 0)
1089 return 0;
1090 d = sym_of_ast(AD_NUMELM(ad));
1091 if (d == stb.i0 || STYPEG(d) != ST_CONST)
1092 return 0;
1093 d = CONVAL2G(d);
1094 return d;
1095}

1097DTYPE
1098dtype_with_shape(DTYPE dtype, int shape)
1099{
1100 int ndim, i, last_mp, last_mp_const;
1101 ISZ_T last_mp_val;
1102 DTYPE dtyper;
1103 /* if the shape is scalar, either return the old scalar datatype
1104 * or the base type if the old datatype was an array */
1105 if (shape == 0 || SHD_NDIM(shape) == 0) {
1106 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
1107 return DTY(dtype + 1);
1108 } else {
1109 return dtype;
1110 }
1111 }
1112 /* if the datatype is an array and the shape has dimensions,
1113 * and the dimensionality and sizes match, no need to change */
1114 ndim = SHD_NDIM(shape);
1115 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
1116 if (ADD_NUMDIM(dtype) == ndim) {
1117 /* check the upper/lower bounds */
1118 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
1119 /* skip if the stride is not one */
1120 if (SHD_STRIDE(shape, i) != astb.bnd.one)
1121 return dtype;
1122 if (SHD_LWB(shape, i) != ADD_LWAST(dtype, i))
1123 break;
1124 if (SHD_UPB(shape, i) != ADD_UPAST(dtype, i))
1125 break;
1126 }
1127 if (i == ndim) {
1128 /* all bounds matched */
1129 return dtype;
1130 }
1131 }
1132 }
1133 /* must make a new datatype */
1134 dtyper = get_array_dtype(ndim, DT_NONE);
1135 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
1136 /* copy base type */
1137 DTY(dtyper + 1) = DTY(dtype + 1);
1138 } else {
1139 /* make this the new base type */
1140 DTY(dtyper + 1) = dtype;
1141 }
1142 last_mp_const = 1;
1143 last_mp_val = 1;
1144 last_mp = astb.bnd.one;
1145 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
1146 int lb, ub;
1147 ISZ_T lbval, ubval;
1148 ADD_LWAST(dtyper, i) = ADD_LWBD(dtyper, i) = SHD_LWB(shape, i);
1149 ADD_UPAST(dtyper, i) = ADD_UPBD(dtyper, i) = SHD_UPB(shape, i);
1150 ADD_EXTNTAST(dtyper, i) =
1151 mk_extent(ADD_LWAST(dtyper, i), ADD_UPAST(dtyper, i), i);
1152 ADD_MLPYR(dtyper, i) = last_mp;
1153 lb = ADD_LWAST(dtyper, i);
1154 if (!A_ALIASG(lb)) {
1155 lb = -1;
1156 } else {
1157 lb = A_ALIASG(lb);
1158 lbval = ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(lb));
1159 }
1160 ub = ADD_UPAST(dtyper, i);
1161 if (!A_ALIASG(ub)) {
1162 ub = -1;
1163 } else {
1164 ub = A_ALIASG(ub);
1165 ubval = ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(ub));
1166 }
1167 if (last_mp_const && lb > 0 && ub > 0) {
1168 last_mp_val = (last_mp_val) * (ubval - lbval + 1);
1169 last_mp = mk_isz_cval(last_mp_val, astb.bnd.dtype);
1170 } else {
1171 last_mp_const = 0;
1172 last_mp = mk_bnd_ast();
1173 }
1174 }
1175
1176 ADD_NUMELM(dtyper) = last_mp;
1177 ADD_ZBASE(dtyper) = mk_bnd_ast();
1178 return dtyper;
1179} /* dtype_with_shape */

1182ad_val_of(int sym)

1184 if (XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
1185 INT num[2];
1186 ISZ_T v;
1187 num[0] = CONVAL1G(sym);
1188 num[1] = CONVAL2G(sym);
1189 INT64_2_ISZ(num, v);
1190 return v;
1191 }

1212int
1213alignment(DTYPE dtype)
1214{
1215 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
1216 int align_val;
1217
1218 switch (ty) {
1219 case TY_DWORD:
1220 case TY_DBLE:
1221 case TY_DCMPLX:
1222 case TY_QCMPLX:
1223 if (!flg.dalign)
1224 return dtypeinfo[TY_INT].align;
1225 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1226 case TY_QUAD:
1227 case TY_WORD:
1228 case TY_HOLL:
1229 case TY_BINT:
1230 case TY_SINT:
1231 case TY_INT:
1232 case TY_REAL:
1233 case TY_CMPLX:
1234 case TY_BLOG:
1235 case TY_SLOG:
1236 case TY_LOG:
1237 case TY_CHAR:
1238 case TY_NCHAR:
1239 case TY_PTR:
1240 return dtypeinfo[ty].align;
1241 case TY_INT8:
1242 case TY_LOG8:
1243 if (!flg.dalign || XBIT(119, 0x100000))
1244 return dtypeinfo[TY_INT].align;
1245 return dtypeinfo[ty].align;
1246
1247 case TY_ARRAY:
1248 align_val = alignment((int)DTY(dtype + 1));
1249 return align_val;
1250
1251 case TY_STRUCT:
1252 case TY_UNION:
1253 case TY_DERIVED:
1254 return DTY(dtype + 4);
1255
1256 default:
1257 interr("alignment: bad dtype ", ty, 3);
1258 return 0;
1259 }
1260}

1262/** \brief Like alignment(), but takes into account whether the var is a pointer
1263 */
1264int
1265alignment_of_var(int sptr)
1266{
1267 DTYPE dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1268 int align;
1269
1270 if (POINTERG(sptr) || ALLOCG(sptr)) {
1271 align = dtypeinfo[TY_PTR].align;
1272 } else {
1273 align = alignment(dtype);
1274 }
1275#ifdef QALNG
1276 if (QALNG(sptr)) {
1277 int ta;
1278 ta = dtypeinfo[TY_QUAD].align;
1279 if (align < ta)
1280 align = ta;
1281 }
1282#endif
1283#ifdef PDALN_IS_DEFAULT
1284 if (!PDALN_IS_DEFAULT(sptr)) {
1285 /* PDALNG==3 means align to 2^3==8 byte address, align == 7 */
1286 int ta = (1 << PDALNG(sptr)) - 1;
1287 if (align < ta)
1288 align = ta;
1289 }
1290#endif
1291 return align;
1292} /* alignment_of_var */

1330/*
1331 * Data structure to hold TY_CHAR entries: linked list off of
1332 * array chartab; entries that are equal module CHARTABSIZE are
1333 * linked. Relative pointers (integers) are used.
1334 */
1335#define CHARTABSIZE 40
1336static int chartab[CHARTABSIZE];
1337struct chartab {
1338 int next;
1339 DTYPE dtype;
1340};
1341static int chartabavail, chartabsize;
1342static struct chartab *chartabbase = 0;
1343
1344void
1345init_chartab(void)
1346{
1347 int i;
1348
1349 for (i = 0; i < CHARTABSIZE; ++i)
1350 chartab[i] = 0;
1351 if (chartabbase == 0) {
1352 /* allocate new */
1353 chartabsize = CHARTABSIZE;
1354 NEW(chartabbase, struct chartab, chartabsize);
1355 }
1356 chartabavail = 1;
1357 chartabbase[0].next = 0;
1358 chartabbase[0].dtype = 0;
1359
1360 rehost_machar(flg.x[45]);
1361
1362 if (XBIT(52, 1)) {
1363 /* complex must be double-aligned */
1364 dtypeinfo[TY_CMPLX].align = dtypeinfo[TY_DBLE].align;
1365 }
1366}

1368void
1369fini_chartab()
1370{
1371 FREE(chartabbase);
1372 chartabsize = 0;
1373 chartabavail = 0;
1374} /* fini_chartab */

1376/** Find or allocate a slot in dtype array for the new datatype. For strings,
1377 * check if the data type is already present.
1378 *
1379 * \param n number of datatype entries we want to occupy
1380 * \param v1 data type
1381 * \param v2 second value, meaning depends on data type, for strings it is
1382 * the length, for pointers - target type, etc
1383 */
1384DTYPE
1385get_type(int n, TY_KIND v1, int v2)
1386{
1387 int i, j;
1388 DTYPE dtype = 0;
1389 LOGICAL is_nchar = FALSE;
1390 is_nchar = (v1 == TY_NCHAR);
1391
1392 /* For a string try to find a matching type first */
1393 if (v1 == TY_CHAR || is_nchar) {
1394 if (v2 < 0 || v2 >= astb.stg_avail) {
1395 interr("char string length is wrong.", v2, 2);
1396 v2 = astb.i1;
1397 }
1398 i = v2 % CHARTABSIZE;
1399 if (chartab[i]) {
1400 /* check list for this length */
1401 for (j = chartab[i]; j != 0; j = chartabbase[j].next) {
1402 int k = chartabbase[j].dtype;
1403 if (DTY(k + 1) == v2 && /* same length */
1404 DTY(k) == v1 /*TY_CHAR vs TY_NCHAR*/) {
1405 dtype = chartabbase[j].dtype;
1406 goto found;
1407 }
1408 }
1409 }
1410 if (v2 == astb.i1) {
1411 if (v1 == TY_CHAR) {
1412 dtype = DT_CHAR;
1413 } else if (v1 == TY_NCHAR) {
1414 dtype = DT_NCHAR;
1415 }
1416 }
1417 }
1418 if (dtype == 0) {
1419 dtype = STG_NEXT_SIZE(stb.dt, n);
1420 DTY(dtype) = v1;
1421 DTY(dtype + 1) = v2;
1422 if (v1 == TY_CHAR || is_nchar) {
1423 /* not found */
1424 NEED(chartabavail + n, chartabbase, struct chartab, chartabsize,
1425 chartabsize + CHARTABSIZE);
1426 chartabbase[chartabavail].dtype = dtype;
1427 chartabbase[chartabavail].next = chartab[i];
1428 chartab[i] = chartabavail++;
1429 }
1430 }
1431found:
1432 return dtype;
1433}

1435/** \brief Return true if the data types for two functions are compatible.
1436
1437 Two functions are compatible if a single local variable can be
1438 used to hold their return values and therefore implying that the
1439 same return mechanism can be used for the functions.
1440 */
1441LOGICAL
1442cmpat_func(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
1443{
1444 if (d1 == d2) {
1445 return TRUE;
1446 } else {
1447 int fv1 = dtypeinfo[DTY(d1)].fval;
1448 int fv2 = dtypeinfo[DTY(d2)].fval;
1449 assert(fv1 >= 0, "cmpat_func1: bad dtype", d1, 3);
1450 assert(fv2 >= 0, "cmpat_func2: bad dtype", d2, 3);
1451 return fv1 == fv2;
1452 }
1453}

1455/** \brief Return TRUE if the scalar data types of an actual argument matches
1456 the formal with respect to the type & kind rules.
1457 */
1458LOGICAL
1459tk_match_arg(int formal_dt, int actual_dt, LOGICAL flag)
1460{
1461 int f_len;
1462 int a_len;
1463 LOGICAL unk = FALSE;
1464 int f_dt = DDTG(formal_dt);
1465 int a_dt = DDTG(actual_dt);
1466
1467 if (DTY(f_dt) == TY_CHAR) {
1468 if (DTY(a_dt) != TY_CHAR)
1469 return FALSE;
1470 /*
1471 * if formal is not assumed length, the length of the formal must be
1472 * be less than or equal to the length of the actual.
1473 */
1474 if (f_dt != DT_ASSCHAR && a_dt != DT_ASSCHAR && f_dt != DT_DEFERCHAR &&
1475 a_dt != DT_DEFERCHAR) {
1476 f_len = DTY(f_dt + 1);
1477 if (!A_ALIASG(f_len)) {
1478 f_len = 0;
1479 } else {
1480 f_len = A_ALIASG(f_len);
1481 f_len = A_SPTRG(f_len);
1482 f_len = CONVAL2G(f_len);
1483 }
1484 a_len = DTY(a_dt + 1);
1485 if (!A_ALIASG(a_len)) {
1486 a_len = 0;
1487 unk = TRUE;
1488 } else {
1489 a_len = A_ALIASG(a_len);
1490 a_len = A_SPTRG(a_len);
1491 a_len = CONVAL2G(a_len);
1492 }
1493 if (DTY(formal_dt) == TY_ARRAY) {
1494 int f_nelems = extent_of(formal_dt);
1495 int a_nelems;
1496 if (DTY(actual_dt) == TY_ARRAY)
1497 a_nelems = extent_of(actual_dt);
1498 else
1499 a_nelems = 1;
1500 if (f_nelems && a_nelems && f_len && a_len) {
1501 if (f_nelems * f_len > a_nelems * a_len)
1502 return FALSE;
1503 }
1504 } else if (!unk && f_len > a_len)
1505 return FALSE;
1506 }
1507 }
1508 else if (DTY(f_dt) == TY_NCHAR) {
1509 if (DTY(a_dt) != TY_NCHAR)
1510 return FALSE;
1511 f_len = DTY(f_dt + 1);
1512 if (!A_ALIASG(f_len)) {
1513 f_len = 0;
1514 unk = TRUE;
1515 } else {
1516 f_len = A_ALIASG(f_len);
1517 f_len = A_SPTRG(f_len);
1518 f_len = CONVAL2G(f_len);
1519 }
1520 a_len = DTY(a_dt + 1);
1521 if (!A_ALIASG(a_len)) {
1522 a_len = 0;
1523 } else {
1524 a_len = A_ALIASG(a_len);
1525 a_len = A_SPTRG(a_len);
1526 a_len = CONVAL2G(a_len);
1527 }
1528 if (f_dt != DT_ASSNCHAR && f_dt != DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
1529 if (!unk && f_len > a_len)
1530 return FALSE;
1531 }
1532 }
1533 else if (!eq_dtype2(f_dt, a_dt, flag)) {
1534 if (DTY(f_dt) == TY_PTR && DTY(a_dt) == TY_PTR &&
1535 DTY(DTY(f_dt + 1)) == TY_PROC && DTY(DTY(a_dt + 1)) == TY_PROC) {
1536 /* eq_dtype2 checks equality of the procedure pointers.
1537 * If they are not the same (including the same name), then
1538 * it returns false. This is correct for an equality test.
1539 * However, in this case, we don't care about the names being
1540 * the same if all other attributes are equal.
1541 */
1542 DTYPE d1 = DTY(f_dt + 1);
1543 DTYPE d2 = DTY(a_dt + 1);
1544 if (cmp_interfaces(DTY(d1 + 2), DTY(d2 + 2), FALSE)) {
1545 return TRUE;
1546 }
1547 }
1548 return FALSE;
1549 }
1550
1551 return TRUE;
1552}

1554#if defined(PARENTG)
1555LOGICAL
1556extends_type(int tg1, int tg2)
1557{
1558 /* Returns true if derived type tag tg2 extends derived type tag tg1 */
1559 int sptr;
1560
1561 if (!tg2 || !tg1 || DTY(DTYPEG(tg1)) != TY_DERIVED ||
1562 DTY(DTYPEG(tg2)) != TY_DERIVED)
1563 return FALSE;
1564 if (strcmp(SYMNAME(tg1), SYMNAME(tg2)) == 0)
1565 return TRUE;
1566 sptr = DTY(DTYPEG(tg2) + 1);
1567 if (PARENTG(sptr))
1568 return extends_type(tg1, sptr);
1569 return FALSE;

1571
1572static LOGICAL
1573same_parameterized_dt(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
1574{
1575
1576 /* Used in conjunction with same_dtype().
1577 * Returns TRUE if both d1 and d2 are the same
1578 * parameterized derived type
1579 */
1580 int base_type1, base_type2, mem1, mem2, val1, val2;
1581 int rslt;
1582
1583 if (d1 == d2)
1584 return TRUE;
1585 if (DTY(d1) == TY_DERIVED && DTY(d2) == TY_DERIVED) {
1586 base_type1 = BASETYPEG(DTY(d1 + 3));
1587 base_type2 = BASETYPEG(DTY(d2 + 3));
1588 if (!base_type1)
1589 base_type1 = d1;
1590 if (!base_type2)
1591 base_type2 = d2;
1592 if (base_type1 && base_type2 && base_type1 == base_type2) {
1593 for (mem1 = DTY(d1 + 1), mem2 = DTY(d2 + 1); mem1 > NOSYM && mem2 > NOSYM;
1594 mem1 = SYMLKG(mem1), mem2 = SYMLKG(mem2)) {
1595 if (PARENTG(mem1)) {
1596 if (!PARENTG(mem2)) {
1597 return FALSE;
1598 }
1599 rslt = same_parameterized_dt(DTYPEG(mem1), DTYPEG(mem2));
1600 if (!rslt)
1601 return FALSE;
1602 } else if (PARENTG(mem2)) {
1603 return FALSE;
1604 }
1605 if (!SETKINDG(mem1) && !USEKINDG(mem1) && KINDG(mem1) &&
1606 PARMINITG(mem1)) {
1607 val1 = PARMINITG(mem1);
1608 } else if (SETKINDG(mem1) && !USEKINDG(mem1) && KINDG(mem1)) {
1609 if (LENPARMG(mem1)) {
1610 val1 = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(LENG(mem1), 0);
1611 if (val1 > 0 && A_TYPEG(val1) == A_CNST) {
1612 val1 = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(val1));
1613 } else {
1614 continue;
1615 }
1616 } else {
1617 val1 = KINDG(mem1);
1618 }
1619 } else {
1620 val1 = 0;
1621 }
1622 if (!SETKINDG(mem2) && !USEKINDG(mem2) && KINDG(mem2) &&
1623 PARMINITG(mem2)) {
1624 val2 = PARMINITG(mem2);
1625 } else if (SETKINDG(mem2) && !USEKINDG(mem2) && KINDG(mem2)) {
1626 if (LENPARMG(mem2)) {
1627 val2 = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(LENG(mem2), 0);
1628 if (val2 > 0 && A_TYPEG(val2) == A_CNST) {
1629 val2 = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(val2));
1630 } else {
1631 continue;
1632 }
1633 } else {
1634 val2 = KINDG(mem2);
1635 }
1636 } else {
1637 val2 = 0;
1638 }
1639 if (val1 != val2) {
1640 return FALSE;
1641 }
1642 }
1643 return TRUE;
1644 }
1645 }
1646 return FALSE;
1647}
1648#endif

1650/** \brief In the presence of modules and interface blocks, it's possible that
1651 two
1652 identical derived types are not represented by the same data type record.
1653 If this occurs, eq_dtype() will check the types of the members.
1654 */
1655LOGICAL
1656eq_dtype2(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2, LOGICAL flag)
1657{
1658 int s1, s2;
1659 int tg1, tg2;
1660
1661 if (d1 == d2)
1662 return TRUE;
1663 if (DTY(d1) != DTY(d2))
1664 return FALSE;
1665 switch (DTY(d1)) {
1666 case TY_ARRAY:
1667 /* check rank and element type */
1668 if (ADD_NUMDIM(d1) != ADD_NUMDIM(d2))
1669 return FALSE;
1670 return (eq_dtype2((int)DTY(d1 + 1), (int)DTY(d2 + 1), flag));
1671
1672 case TY_DERIVED:
1673 tg1 = DTY(d1 + 3);
1674 tg2 = DTY(d2 + 3);
1675 if (tg1 == tg2)
1676 /* tags are the same => equal types */
1677 return TRUE;
1678#if defined(PARENTG)
1679 if (flag && extends_type(tg1, tg2)) /* type extension */
1680 return TRUE;
1681#endif
1682 if (same_parameterized_dt(d1, d2))
1683 return TRUE;
1684 if (strcmp(SYMNAME(tg1), SYMNAME(tg2)) != 0)
1685 return FALSE;
1686
1687 if (VISITG(tg1) && VISITG(tg2)) {
1688 /* have a self-referential derived type */
1689 return TRUE;
1690 }
1691 if (VISITG(tg1) || VISITG(tg2)) {
1692 return FALSE;
1693 }
1694 VISITP(tg1, 1);
1695 VISITP(tg2, 1);
1696 /* traverse the members */
1697 for (s1 = DTY(d1 + 1), s2 = DTY(d2 + 1); s1 > NOSYM && s2 > NOSYM;
1698 s1 = SYMLKG(s1), s2 = SYMLKG(s2)) {
1699 if (HCCSYMG(s1) && HCCSYMG(s2)) {
1700 } else if (HCCSYMG(s1) || HCCSYMG(s2)) {
1701 break; /* return FALSE; */
1702 } else if (strcmp(SYMNAME(s1), SYMNAME(s2)) != 0)
1703 break; /* return FALSE; */
1704 /* if one member is private, both must be */
1705 if (PRIVATEG(s1) != PRIVATEG(s2))
1706 break; /* return FALSE; */
1707 /* member types are different => different types */
1708 if (!eq_dtype2(DTYPEG(s1), DTYPEG(s2), flag))
1709 break; /* return FALSE; */
1710 }
1711 VISITP(tg1, 0);
1712 VISITP(tg2, 0);
1713 /* more members in either record? */
1714 if (s2 > NOSYM || s1 > NOSYM)
1715 return FALSE;
1716 return TRUE;
1717
1718 case TY_CHAR:
1719 case TY_NCHAR:
1720 /* compare lengths */
1721 if (DTY(d1 + 1) == DTY(d2 + 1))
1722 return TRUE;
1723 break;
1724
1725 case TY_PTR:
1726 if (DTY(DTY(d1 + 1)) == TY_PROC) {
1727 return eq_dtype2(DTY(d1 + 1), DTY(d2 + 1), flag);
1728 }
1729 break;
1730 case TY_PROC:
1731 if ((DTY(d1 + 2) && (DTY(d1 + 2) == DTY(d2 + 2))) ||
1732 (cmp_interfaces(DTY(d1 + 2), DTY(d2 + 2), TRUE))) {
1733 /* identical interfaces */
1734 return TRUE;
1735 }
1736 if (!DTY(d1 + 2) && !DTY(d1 + 2)) {
1737 /* no interfaces; check result dtypes */
1738 return eq_dtype2(DTY(d1 + 1), DTY(d2 + 1), flag);
1739 }
1740 break;
1741 default:
1742 break;
1743 }
1744 return FALSE;
1745}
1746
1747LOGICAL
1748eq_dtype(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
1749{
1750 return eq_dtype2(d1, d2, FALSE);
1751}
1752
1753/** \brief Check to see if two types are extensions from the same ancestor */
1754LOGICAL
1755same_ancestor(DTYPE dtype1, DTYPE dtype2)
1756{
1757 int mem1, mem2;
1758 int next_dtype1, next_dtype2;
1759
1760 if (DTY(dtype1) == TY_ARRAY)
1761 dtype1 = DTY(dtype1 + 1);
1762
1763 if (DTY(dtype2) == TY_ARRAY)
1764 dtype2 = DTY(dtype2 + 1);
1765
1766 if (DTY(dtype1) != TY_DERIVED || DTY(dtype2) != TY_DERIVED)
1767 return FALSE;
1768
1769 if (eq_dtype2(dtype1, dtype2, 1) || eq_dtype2(dtype2, dtype1, 1))
1770 return TRUE;
1771
1772 mem1 = DTY(dtype1 + 1);
1773 mem2 = DTY(dtype2 + 1);
1774
1775 if (PARENTG(mem1))
1776 next_dtype1 = DTYPEG(mem1);
1777 else
1778 next_dtype1 = dtype1;
1779
1780 if (PARENTG(mem2))
1781 next_dtype2 = DTYPEG(mem2);
1782 else
1783 next_dtype2 = dtype2;
1784
1785 if (dtype1 == next_dtype1 && dtype2 == next_dtype2)
1786 return FALSE;
1787
1788 return same_ancestor(next_dtype1, next_dtype2);
1789}

1890/** \brief Similar to eq_dtype(), except all scalar integer types are compatible
1891 with
1892 each other, all scalar logical types are compatible with each other, all
1893 character types are compatible with each other.
1894 */
1895LOGICAL
1896cmpat_dtype(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
1897{
1898 if (d1 == d2)
1899 return TRUE;
1900 if (DTY(d1) != DTY(d2)) {
1901 /* check for any logical first since logical types also have the
1902 * _TY_INT attribute.
1903 */
1904 if (DT_ISLOG(d1) && DT_ISLOG(d2))
1905 return TRUE;
1906 if (DT_ISINT(d1) && DT_ISINT(d2))
1907 return TRUE;
1908 return FALSE;
1909 }
1910 if (DTY(d1) == TY_CHAR || DTY(d1) == TY_NCHAR)
1911 return TRUE;
1912 return eq_dtype(d1, d2);
1913}
1914
1915/** \brief Similar to compat_dtype(), except all scalar integer types are
1916 compatible with each other, all scalar logical types are compatible
1917 with each other, all character types are compatible with each other.
1918 Also, array extents are checked.
1919 */
1920LOGICAL
1921cmpat_dtype_with_size(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
1922{
1923 int s1, s2, i, n;
1924
1925 if (is_iso_cptr(d1)) {
1926 d1 = DTYPEG(DTY(d1 + 1));
1927 }
1928 if (is_iso_cptr(d2)) {
1929 d2 = DTYPEG(DTY(d2 + 1));
1930 }
1931
1932 if (d1 == d2)
1933 return TRUE;
1934 if (d1 <= 0 || d2 <= 0)
1935 return FALSE;
1936 if (DTY(d1) != DTY(d2)) {
1937 /* check for any logical first since logical types also have the
1938 * _TY_INT attribute.
1939 */
1940 if (DT_ISLOG(d1) && DT_ISLOG(d2))
1941 return TRUE;
1942 if (DT_ISNUMERIC(d2) && DT_ISNUMERIC(d1))
1943 return TRUE;
1944 /* allow array of blah to match with scalar blah */
1945 if (DTY(d1) == TY_ARRAY && cmpat_dtype_with_size(DTY(d1 + 1), d2))
1946 return TRUE;
1947 if (DTY(d2) == TY_ARRAY && cmpat_dtype_with_size(d1, DTY(d2 + 1)))
1948 return TRUE;
1949 return FALSE;
1950 }
1951 /* here, DTY(d1) == DTY(d2) */
1952 if (DTY(d1) == TY_CHAR || DTY(d1) == TY_NCHAR)
1953 return TRUE;
1954 switch (DTY(d1)) {
1955 case TY_ARRAY:
1956 /* check rank, extents and element type */
1957 if (ADD_NUMDIM(d1) != ADD_NUMDIM(d2))
1958 return FALSE;
1959 n = ADD_NUMDIM(d1);
1960 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1961 /* check bounds */
1962 int l1, l2, u1, u2, e1, e2;
1963 l1 = ADD_LWBD(d1, i);
1964 u1 = ADD_UPBD(d1, i);
1965 l2 = ADD_LWBD(d2, i);
1966 u2 = ADD_UPBD(d2, i);
1967 /* if not constant upper bound, give up */
1968 if (!u1 || !A_ALIASG(u1))
1969 continue;
1970 if (A_DTYPEG(u1) != DT_INT4)
1971 continue;
1972 e1 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(u1));
1973 if (l1) {
1974 if (!A_ALIASG(l1))
1975 continue;
1976 if (A_DTYPEG(l1) != DT_INT4)
1977 continue;
1978 e1 -= get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(l1)) - 1;
1979 }
1980 if (!u2 || !A_ALIASG(u2))
1981 continue;
1982 if (A_DTYPEG(u2) != DT_INT4)
1983 continue;
1984 e2 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(u2));
1985 if (l2) {
1986 if (!A_ALIASG(l2))
1987 continue;
1988 if (A_DTYPEG(l2) != DT_INT4)
1989 continue;
1990 e2 -= get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(l2)) - 1;
1991 }
1992 /* different extents */
1993 if (e1 != e2)
1994 return FALSE;
1995 }
1996 return cmpat_dtype_with_size(DTY(d1 + 1), DTY(d2 + 1));
1997
1998 case TY_DERIVED:
1999 /* tags are the same => equal types */
2000 if (DTY(d1 + 3) == DTY(d2 + 3))
2001 return TRUE;
2002 /* traverse the members */
2003 for (s1 = DTY(d1 + 1), s2 = DTY(d2 + 1); s1 > NOSYM && s2 > NOSYM;
2004 s1 = SYMLKG(s1), s2 = SYMLKG(s2)) {
2005 /* member types are different => different types */
2006 if (!cmpat_dtype_with_size(DTYPEG(s1), DTYPEG(s2)))
2007 return FALSE;
2008 if (PRIVATEG(s1) != PRIVATEG(s2))
2009 return FALSE;
2010 }
2011 /* more members in either record? */
2012 if (s2 > NOSYM || s1 > NOSYM)
2013 return FALSE;
2014 return TRUE;
2015
2016 case TY_CHAR:
2017 case TY_NCHAR:
2018 return TRUE;
2019 default:
2020 break;
2021 }
2022 return FALSE;
2023}
2024
2025/** \brief Similar to eq_dtype(), except types must match exactly,
2026 and derived types must be SEQUENCE and match in name also.
2027 Also, array extents are checked.
2028 */
2029LOGICAL
2030same_dtype(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
2031{
2032 int s1, s2, i, n;
2033 int tg1, tg2;
2034
2035 if (d1 == d2)
2036 return TRUE;
2037 if (d1 <= 0 || d2 <= 0)
2038 return FALSE;
2039 if (DTY(d1) != DTY(d2))
2040 return FALSE;
2041 /* here, DTY(d1) == DTY(d2) */
2042 switch (DTY(d1)) {
2043 case TY_ARRAY:
2044 /* check rank, extents and element type */
2045 if (ADD_NUMDIM(d1) != ADD_NUMDIM(d2))
2046 return FALSE;
2047 n = ADD_NUMDIM(d1);
2048 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
2049 /* check bounds */
2050 int l1, l2, u1, u2, e1, e2;
2051 l1 = ADD_LWBD(d1, i);
2052 u1 = ADD_UPBD(d1, i);
2053 l2 = ADD_LWBD(d2, i);
2054 u2 = ADD_UPBD(d2, i);
2055 /* if not constant upper bound, give up */
2056 if (!u1 || !A_ALIASG(u1))
2057 continue;
2058 if (A_DTYPEG(u1) != DT_INT4)
2059 continue;
2060 e1 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(u1));
2061 if (l1) {
2062 if (!A_ALIASG(l1))
2063 continue;
2064 if (A_DTYPEG(l1) != DT_INT4)
2065 continue;
2066 e1 -= get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(l1)) - 1;
2067 }
2068 if (!u2 || !A_ALIASG(u2))
2069 continue;
2070 if (A_DTYPEG(u2) != DT_INT4)
2071 continue;
2072 e2 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(u2));
2073 if (l2) {
2074 if (!A_ALIASG(l2))
2075 continue;
2076 if (A_DTYPEG(l2) != DT_INT4)
2077 continue;
2078 e2 -= get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(l2)) - 1;
2079 }
2080 /* different extents */
2081 if (e1 != e2)
2082 return FALSE;
2083 }
2084 return same_dtype(DTY(d1 + 1), DTY(d2 + 1));
2085
2086 case TY_DERIVED:
2087 /* tags are the same => equal types */
2088 tg1 = DTY(d1 + 3);
2089 tg2 = DTY(d2 + 3);
2090 if (tg1 == tg2)
2091 return TRUE;
2092 /* both must be SEQUENCE or both must be BIND(C) */
2093 if ((SEQG(tg1) && SEQG(tg2)) || (CFUNCG(tg1) && CFUNCG(tg2)))
2094 ;
2095 else if (same_parameterized_dt(d1, d2))
2096 return TRUE;
2097 else {
2098 return FALSE;
2099 }
2100 if (VISITG(tg1) && VISITG(tg2)) {
2101 /* have a self-referential derived type */
2102 return TRUE;
2103 }
2104 if (VISITG(tg1) || VISITG(tg2)) {
2105 return FALSE;
2106 }
2107 VISITP(tg1, 1);
2108 VISITP(tg2, 1);
2109 /* traverse the members */
2110 for (s1 = DTY(d1 + 1), s2 = DTY(d2 + 1); s1 > NOSYM && s2 > NOSYM;
2111 s1 = SYMLKG(s1), s2 = SYMLKG(s2)) {
2112 /* neither member can be PRIVATE */
2113 if (PRIVATEG(s1) || PRIVATEG(s2))
2114 break; /* return FALSE; */
2115 /* member types are different => different types */
2116 if (!same_dtype(DTYPEG(s1), DTYPEG(s2)))
2117 break; /* return FALSE; */
2118 }
2119 VISITP(tg1, 0);
2120 VISITP(tg2, 0);
2121 /* more members in either record? */
2122 if (s2 > NOSYM || s1 > NOSYM)
2123 return FALSE;
2124 return TRUE;
2125
2126 case TY_CHAR:
2127 case TY_NCHAR:
2128 /* compare lengths */
2129 if (DTY(d1 + 1) == DTY(d2 + 1))
2130 return TRUE;
2131 break;
2132
2133 default:
2134 break;
2135 }
2136 return FALSE;
2137}

2139/** \brief Similar to eq_dtype(), except all scalar integer types are compatible
2140 with each other, all scalar logical types are compatible with each other,
2141 all character types are compatible with each other and we allow
2142 casting arrays when types fit into each other.
2143 */
2144LOGICAL
2145cmpat_dtype_array_cast(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
2146{
2147 if (d1 == d2)
2148 return TRUE;
2149 if (DTY(d1) != DTY(d2)) {
2150 /* check for any logical first since logical types also have the
2151 * _TY_INT attribute.
2152 */
2153 if (DT_ISLOG(d1) && DT_ISLOG(d2))
2154 return TRUE;
2155 if (DT_ISINT(d1) && DT_ISINT(d2))
2156 return TRUE;
2157 return FALSE;
2158 }
2159
2160 /* At this place DTY(d1) = DTY(d2) */
2161 if (DTY(d1) == TY_CHAR || DTY(d1) == TY_NCHAR)
2162 return TRUE;
2163
2164 /* Perform checks for array casting possibilities */
2165 if (DTY(d1) == TY_ARRAY) {
2166 DTYPE array_type_1 = DDTG(d1);
2167 DTYPE array_type_2 = DDTG(d2);
2168
2169 /* We want to allow all casts apart from REAL to INT without further checks */
2170 if ((DT_ISINT(array_type_1) && DT_ISINT(array_type_2)) ||
2171 (DT_ISREAL(array_type_1) && DT_ISREAL(array_type_2)) ||
2172 (DT_ISREAL(array_type_1) && DT_ISINT(array_type_2)))
2173 return true; // cngcon will later check if numbers actually fit into each other and warn if not
2174 else
2175 /* Not REAL or INT, continue normal checks */
2176 return cmpat_dtype(array_type_1, array_type_2);
2177 }
2178
2179 /* Continue checks for other cases */
2180 return eq_dtype(d1, d2);
2181}

2183static int
2184priority(int op)
2185{
2186 switch (op) {
2187 case OP_CMP:
2188 case OP_AIF:
2189 case OP_FUNC:
2190 case OP_CON:
2191 case OP_LOG:
2192 /* I don't know what these are, anyway */
2193 return 0;
2194 /* missing priority 110 is for user-defined binary operators */
2195 case OP_LEQV:
2196 case OP_LNEQV:
2197 return 20;
2198 case OP_LOR:
2199 return 30;
2200 case OP_LAND:
2201 return 40;
2202 case OP_LNOT:
2203 return 50;
2204 case OP_EQ:
2205 case OP_GE:
2206 case OP_GT:
2207 case OP_LE:
2208 case OP_LT:
2209 case OP_NE:
2210 return 60;
2211 case OP_CAT:
2212 return 70;
2213 case OP_NEG:
2214 case OP_ADD:
2215 case OP_SUB:
2216 return 80;
2217 case OP_MUL:
2218 case OP_DIV:
2219 return 90;
2220 case OP_XTOI:
2221 case OP_XTOX:
2222 return 101; /* right associative */
2223 /* missing priority 110 is for user-defined unary operators */
2224 case OP_LD:
2225 case OP_ST:
2226 case OP_LOC:
2227 case OP_REF:
2228 case OP_VAL:
2229 case OP_BYVAL:
2230 case OP_SCAND:
2231 return 120;
2232 }
2233 interr("priority. Unexpected op", op, 2);
2234 return 0;
2235} /* priority */

2237static int
2238leftparens(int ast, int astleft)
2239{
2240 int prio, prioleft;
2241 if (A_TYPEG(ast) != A_BINOP && A_TYPEG(ast) != A_UNOP) {
2242 return FALSE;
2243 }
2244 if (A_TYPEG(astleft) != A_BINOP && A_TYPEG(astleft) != A_UNOP) {
2245 return FALSE;
2246 }
2247 prio = priority(A_OPTYPEG(ast));
2248 prioleft = priority(A_OPTYPEG(astleft));
2249 if (prio < prioleft)
2250 return FALSE;
2251 if (prioleft < prio)
2252 return TRUE;
2253 /* if the same priority, check if the operator is right-associative */
2254 if (prio & 0x1)
2255 return TRUE;
2256 return FALSE;
2257} /* leftparens */
2258
2259static int
2260rightparens(int ast, int astright)
2261{
2262 int prio, prioright;
2263 if (A_TYPEG(ast) != A_BINOP && A_TYPEG(ast) != A_UNOP) {
2264 return FALSE;
2265 }
2266 if (A_TYPEG(astright) != A_BINOP && A_TYPEG(astright) != A_UNOP) {
2267 return FALSE;
2268 }
2269 prio = priority(A_OPTYPEG(ast));
2270 prioright = priority(A_OPTYPEG(astright));
2271 if (prio < prioright)
2272 return FALSE;
2273 if (prioright < prio)
2274 return TRUE;
2275 /* if the same priority, check if the operator is right-associative */
2276 if (prio & 0x1)
2277 return FALSE;
2278 return TRUE;
2279} /* rightparens */

2386/** \brief Given an AST and a string pointer, append a printable representation
2387 of the AST expression onto the string */
2388void
2389getast(int ast, char *string)
2390{
2391 int asd, ndim, i, lp, rp;
2392 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
2393 case A_ID:
2394 case A_LABEL:
2395 case A_ENTRY:
2396 case A_CNST:
2397 strcat(string, getprint(sym_of_ast(ast)));
2398 if (DBGBIT(5, 0x40) && A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID) {
2399 char b[64];
2400 sprintf(b, "\\%d", sym_of_ast(ast));
2401 strcat(string, b);
2402 }
2403 break;
2404 case A_SUBSCR:
2405 /*strcat( string, getprint(sym_of_ast(ast)) );*/
2406 getast((int)A_LOPG(ast), string);
2407 strcat(string, "(");
2408 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
2409 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
2410 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
2411 if (i)
2412 strcat(string, ",");
2413 getast((int)ASD_SUBS(asd, i), string);
2414 }
2415 strcat(string, ")");
2416 break;
2417 case A_MEM:
2418 getast((int)A_PARENTG(ast), string);
2419 strcat(string, "%");
2420 getast((int)A_MEMG(ast), string);
2421 break;
2422 case A_BINOP:
2423 lp = rp = 0;
2424 if (leftparens(ast, A_LOPG(ast))) {
2425 strcat(string, "(");
2426 lp = 1;
2427 }
2428 getast((int)A_LOPG(ast), string);
2429 if (lp)
2430 strcat(string, ")");
2431 getop(A_OPTYPEG(ast), string);
2432 if (rightparens(ast, A_ROPG(ast))) {
2433 strcat(string, "(");
2434 rp = 1;
2435 }
2436 getast((int)A_ROPG(ast), string);
2437 if (rp)
2438 strcat(string, ")");
2439 break;
2440 case A_UNOP:
2441 rp = 0;
2442 getop(A_OPTYPEG(ast), string);
2443 if (rightparens(ast, A_LOPG(ast))) {
2444 strcat(string, "(");
2445 rp = 1;
2446 }
2447 getast((int)A_LOPG(ast), string);
2448 if (rp)
2449 strcat(string, ")");
2450 break;
2451 case A_PAREN:
2452 strcat(string, "(");
2453 getast((int)A_LOPG(ast), string);
2454 strcat(string, ")");
2455 break;
2456 case A_CONV:
2457 strcat(string, "conv(");
2458 getast((int)A_LOPG(ast), string);
2459 strcat(string, ")");
2460 break;
2461 case A_CMPLXC:
2462 strcat(string, "(");
2463 getast((int)A_LOPG(ast), string);
2464 strcat(string, ",");
2465 getast((int)A_ROPG(ast), string);
2466 strcat(string, ")");
2467 break;
2468 default:
2469 strcat(string, "??");
2470 break;
2471 } /* switch */
2472} /* getast */

2474/** \brief Check if ast is deferred-length character */
2475bool
2476is_deferlenchar_ast(int ast)
2477{
2478 DTYPE dt;
2479 SPTR sym = 0;
2480
2481 dt = DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast));
2482 if (DTY(dt) != TY_CHAR && DTY(dt) != TY_NCHAR) {
2483 return false;
2484 }
2485
2486 if (dt == DT_ASSCHAR || dt == DT_ASSNCHAR) {
2487 return false;
2488 } else if (dt == DT_DEFERCHAR || dt == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
2489 return true;
2490 }
2491
2492 if (ast_is_sym(ast)) {
2493 sym = memsym_of_ast(ast);
2494 }
2495
2496 /* adjustable length character */
2497 if ((sym > NOSYM) && ADJLENG(sym)) {
2498 return false;
2499 }
2500
2501 if (DTY(A_DTYPEG(ast)) == TY_ARRAY) {
2502 if (ADD_DEFER(A_DTYPEG(ast))) {
2503 dt = DTY(DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast)) + 1);
2504 if (A_TYPEG(dt) != A_CNST) {
2505 return true;
2506 }
2507 }
2508 }
2509 return false;
2510}
2511
2512/** \brief Check if dtype is deferred-length character */
2513bool
2514is_deferlenchar_dtype(DTYPE dtype)
2515{
2516 DTYPE dt;
2517
2518 dt = DDTG(dtype);
2519 if (DTY(dt) != TY_CHAR && DTY(dt) != TY_NCHAR) {
2520 return false;
2521 }
2522
2523 if (dt == DT_DEFERCHAR || dt == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
2524 return true;
2525 }
2526 dt = DTY(dt+1);
2527 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
2528 if (!ADD_DEFER(dtype)) {
2529 return false;
2530 }
2531 }
2532
2533 if (A_TYPEG(dt) == A_ID) {
2534 /* i.e. character(len=newlen) */
2535 if (ASSNG(A_SPTRG(dt))) {
2536 return true;
2537 }
2538 } else if (A_TYPEG(dt) == A_SUBSCR) {
2539 /* i.e. character(len=newlen(1)) */
2540 if (ASSNG(memsym_of_ast(dt))) {
2541 return true;
2542 }
2543 }
2544
2545 /* i.e. character(len=len(a)) */
2546 if ((A_TYPEG(dt) == A_FUNC || A_TYPEG(dt) == A_INTR)
2547 && is_deferlenchar_ast(ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(dt), 0))) {
2548 return true;
2549 }
2550 return false;
2551}

2554/** \brief Put into the character array pointed to by ptr, the print
2555 representation
2556 of dtype.
2557 */
2558void
2559getdtype(DTYPE dtype, char *ptr)
2560{
2561 int i;
2562 ADSC *ad;
2563 int numdim;
2564 char *p;
2565
2566 p = ptr;
2567 *p = 0;
2568 for (; dtype != 0 && p - ptr <= 150; dtype = DTY(dtype + 1)) {
2569 if (dtype <= 0 || dtype >= stb.dt.stg_avail) {
2570 sprintf(p, "bad dtype(%d)", dtype);
2571 break;
2572 }
2573 if (DTY(dtype) <= 0 || DTY(dtype) > TY_MAX) {
2574 sprintf(p, "bad dtype(%d[%d])", dtype, (int)DTY(dtype));
2575 break;
2576 }
2577 strcpy(p, stb.tynames[DTY(dtype)]);
2578 p += strlen(p);
2579
2580 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
2581 case TY_STRUCT:
2582 case TY_UNION:
2583 case TY_DERIVED:
2584 i = DTY(dtype + 3);
2585 if (i) {
2586 if (i <= NOSYM || i >= stb.stg_avail) {
2587 sprintf(p, "/bad tag=%d/", i);
2588 } else {
2589 sprintf(p, "/%s/", SYMNAME(i));
2590 }
2591 p += strlen(p);
2592 }
2593 return;
2594
2595 case TY_ARRAY:
2596 if (DTY(dtype + 2) == 0) {
2597 *p++ = ' ';
2598 *p++ = '(';
2599 } else {
2600 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
2601 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
2602 if (numdim < 1 || numdim > 7) {
2603 sprintf(p, "ndim=%d", numdim);
2604 numdim = 0;
2605 p += strlen(p);
2606 }
2607 if (AD_DEFER(ad)) {
2608 strcpy(p, " deferred");
2609 p += strlen(p);
2610 }
2611 if (AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) == 1) {
2612 strcpy(p, " assumedshape");
2613 p += strlen(p);
2614 }
2615 if (AD_ASSUMRANK(ad) == 1) {
2616 strcpy(p, " assumedrank");
2617 p += strlen(p);
2618 }
2619 if (AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) == 2) {
2620 strcpy(p, " wasassumedshape");
2621 p += strlen(p);
2622 }
2623 if (AD_ADJARR(ad)) {
2624 strcpy(p, " adjustable");
2625 p += strlen(p);
2626 }
2627 if (AD_ASSUMSZ(ad)) {
2628 strcpy(p, " assumedsize");
2629 p += strlen(p);
2630 }
2631 if (AD_NOBOUNDS(ad)) {
2632 strcpy(p, " nobounds");
2633 p += strlen(p);
2634 }
2635 *p++ = ' ';
2636 *p++ = '(';
2637 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
2638 if (i)
2639 *p++ = ',';
2640 if (AD_LWAST(ad, i)) {
2641 *p = '\0';
2642 getast(AD_LWAST(ad, i), p);
2643 p += strlen(p);
2644 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i) != AD_LWAST(ad, i)) {
2645 *p++ = '[';
2646 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i)) {
2647 *p = '\0';
2648 getast(AD_LWBD(ad, i), p);
2649 p += strlen(p);
2650 }
2651 *p++ = ']';
2652 }
2653 *p++ = ':';
2654 } else if (AD_LWBD(ad, i)) {
2655 *p++ = '[';
2656 *p = '\0';
2657 getast(AD_LWBD(ad, i), p);
2658 p += strlen(p);
2659 *p++ = ']';
2660 *p++ = ':';
2661 }
2662 if (AD_UPAST(ad, i)) {
2663 *p = '\0';
2664 getast(AD_UPAST(ad, i), p);
2665 p += strlen(p);
2666 } else {
2667 *p++ = '*';
2668 }
2669 if (AD_UPBD(ad, i) != AD_UPAST(ad, i)) {
2670 *p++ = '[';
2671 if (AD_UPBD(ad, i)) {
2672 *p = '\0';
2673 getast(AD_UPBD(ad, i), p);
2674 p += strlen(p);
2675 }
2676 *p++ = ']';
2677 }
2678 }
2679 }
2680 strcpy(p, ") of ");
2681 p += 5;
2682 break;
2683
2684 case TY_PTR:
2685 *p++ = ' ';
2686 break;
2687
2688 case TY_CHAR:
2689 case TY_NCHAR:
2690 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR)
2691 sprintf(p, "*(*)");
2692 else if (dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
2693 sprintf(p, "*(:)");
2694 } else {
2695 sprintf(p, "*");
2696 p += strlen(p);
2697 *p = '\0';
2698 getast(DTY(dtype + 1), p);
2699 }
2700 return;
2701
2702 default:
2703 return;
2704 }
2705 }
2706}

2724int
2725dlen(int ty)
2726{
2727 switch (ty) {
2728 case TY_NONE:

2949/** \brief Compute the size of a data type.
2950
2951 This machine dependent routine computes the size of a data type
2952 in terms of two quantities:
2953 - size - number of elements in the data type (returned thru size).
2954 - scale - number of bytes in each element, expressed as a power
2955 of two (the return value of scale_of).
2956
2957 This routine will be used to take advantage of the machines that
2958 have the ability to add a scaled expression (multiplied by a power
2959 of two) to an address. This is particularly useful for incrementing
2960 a pointer variable and array subscripting.
2961
2962 Note that for those machines that do not have this feature, scale_of
2963 returns a scale of 0 and size_of for size.
2964 */
2965int
2966scale_of(DTYPE dtype, INT *size)
2967{
2968 INT d;
2969 int tmp;
2970 int scale, clen;
2971 INT tmpsiz;
2972 TY_KIND ty = get_ty_kind(dtype);
2973
2974 switch (ty) {
2975 case TY_WORD:
2976 case TY_DWORD:
2977 case TY_LOG:
2978 case TY_INT:
2979 case TY_FLOAT:
2980 case TY_PTR:
2981 case TY_SLOG:
2982 case TY_SINT:
2983 case TY_BINT:
2984 case TY_BLOG:
2985 case TY_DBLE:
2986 case TY_CMPLX:
2987 case TY_DCMPLX:
2988 case TY_QCMPLX:
2989 case TY_INT8:
2990 case TY_LOG8:
2991 scale = dtypeinfo[ty].scale;
2992 *size = (unsigned)dtypeinfo[ty].size >> scale;
2993 return scale;
2994
2995 case TY_HOLL:
2996 case TY_CHAR:
2997 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR)
2998 interr("scale_of: attempt to size assumed size character", 0, 3);
2999 clen = string_length(dtype);
3000 *size = clen;
3001 return 0;
3002
3003 case TY_NCHAR:
3004 if (dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR)
3005 interr("scale_of: attempt to size assumed size ncharacter", 0, 3);
3006 clen = string_length(dtype);
3007 *size = 2 * clen;
3008 return 0;
3009
3010 case TY_ARRAY:
3011 if ((d = DTY(dtype + 2)) <= 0) {
3012 interr("scale_of: no array descriptor", (int)d, 3);
3013 d = DTY(dtype + 2) = 1;
3014 }
3015 tmp = scale_of((int)DTY(dtype + 1), &tmpsiz);
3016 *size = d * tmpsiz;
3017 return tmp;
3018
3019 case TY_STRUCT:
3020 case TY_UNION:
3021 case TY_DERIVED:
3022 if (DTY(dtype + 2) <= 0) {
3023 interr("scale_of: 0 size struct", 0, 3);
3024 *size = 4;
3025 return 0;
3026 } else {
3027 *size = DTY(dtype + 2);
3028 return 0;
3029 }
3030
3031 default:
3032 interr("scale_of: bad dtype", ty, 3);
3033 *size = 1;
3034 return 0;
3035 }
3036}

3055#define SS2 0x8e
3056#define SS3 0x8f
3057
3058/** \brief Return number of kanji characters
3059 \param p character string
3060 \param len length in bytes of \p p
3061 */
3062int
3063kanji_len(unsigned char *p, int len)
3064{
3065 int count = 0;
3066 int val;
3067
3068 while (len > 0) {
3069 val = *p;
3070 count++;
3071 if ((val & 0x80) == 0 || len <= 1) /* ASCII */
3072 len--, p++;
3073 else if (val == SS2) /* JIS 8-bit character */
3074 len -= 2, p += 2;
3075 else if (val == SS3 && len >= 3) /* Graphic Character */
3076 len -= 3, p += 3;
3077 else /* Kanji */
3078 len -= 2, p += 2;
3079 }
3080
3081 return count;
3082}
3083
3084/** \brief Extract necessary bytes from character string in order to return
3085 integer (16-bit) representation of one kanji char.
3086 \param p ptr to EUC string
3087 \param len number of bytes in \p p
3088 \param bytes return number of EUC bytes used up
3089*/
3090int
3091kanji_char(unsigned char *p, int len, int *bytes)
3092{
3093 int val = *p;
3094
3095 if ((val & 0x80) == 0 || len <= 1) /* ASCII */
3096 *bytes = 1;
3097 else if (val == SS2) /* JIS 8-bit character */
3098 *bytes = 2, val = *(p + 1);
3099 else if (val == SS3 && len >= 3) /* Graphic Character */
3100 *bytes = 3, val = ((*(p + 1) << 8) | (*(p + 2) & 0x7F));
3101 else /* Kanji */
3102 *bytes = 2, val = ((val << 8) | *(p + 1));
3103
3104 return val;
3105}
3106
3107/** \brief Return number of bytes required for newlen chars.
3108 \param p ptr to EUC string
3109 \param newlen number of kanji chars required from string prefix
3110 \param len total number of bytes in string
3111 */
3112int
3113kanji_prefix(unsigned char *p, int newlen, int len)
3114{
3115 unsigned char *begin;
3116 int bytes;
3117
3118 begin = p;
3119 while (newlen-- > 0) {
3120 (void)kanji_char(p, len, &bytes);
3121 p += bytes;
3122 len -= bytes;
3123 }
3124
3125 return (p - begin);
3126}

3128#define _FP 4
3129#define _VP 6
3130/** \brief Create a dtype record for an array of rank numdim including its array
3131 descriptor.
3132 \param numdim number of dimensions
3133 \param eltype data type of the array element
3134
3135 The layout of an array descriptor is:
3136 <pre>
3137 int numdim; --+
3138 int zbase; |
3139 UINT16 *ilmp; |
3140 char defer; +-- 4 ints (fixed part)
3141 char adjarr; |
3142 char assumsz; |
3143 char pad; --+
3144 struct {
3145 int mlpyr; --+
3146 int lwbd; |
3147 int upbd; +-- 6 ints (variable part)
3148 int lwast; |
3149 int upast; |
3150 int exntnast;-+
3151 } b[numdim];
3152 int numelm; --+-- 1 int
3153 </pre>
3154 Any change in the size of the structure requires a change to one or both
3155 of the macros _FP and _VP. Also the size assertion in symtab.c needs
3156 to be changed.
3157 */
3158DTYPE
3159get_array_dtype(int numdim, DTYPE eltype)
3160{
3161 DTYPE dtype;
3162
3163 dtype = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, eltype);
3164 get_aux_arrdsc(dtype, numdim);
3165
3166 return dtype;
3167}

3169void
3170get_aux_arrdsc(DTYPE dtype, int numdim)
3171{
3172 ADSC *ad;
3173
3174 DTY(dtype + 2) = aux.arrdsc_avl;
3175 aux.arrdsc_avl += (_FP + 1) + (_VP * numdim);
3176 NEED(aux.arrdsc_avl, aux.arrdsc_base, int, aux.arrdsc_size,
3177 aux.arrdsc_avl + 240);
3178 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3179 BZERO(ad, int, (_FP + 1) + _VP * numdim);
3180 AD_NUMDIM(ad) = numdim;
3181}

3184 */

3186dup_array_dtype(DTYPE o_dt)
3187{
3188 ADSC *ad;
3189 ADSC *o_ad = AD_DPTR(o_dt);
3190 int numdim = AD_NUMDIM(o_ad);
3191 DTYPE dtype = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, DT_NONE);
3192
3193 DTY(dtype + 2) = aux.arrdsc_avl;
3194 aux.arrdsc_avl += (_FP + 1) + (_VP * numdim);
3195 NEED(aux.arrdsc_avl, aux.arrdsc_base, int, aux.arrdsc_size,
3196 aux.arrdsc_avl + 240);
3197 o_ad = AD_DPTR(o_dt); /* recreate pointer after possible realloc */
3198 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3199
3200 BCOPY(ad, o_ad, int, (_FP + 1) + _VP * numdim);
3201
3202 /* make it the same element type; the caller may change the type */
3203 DTY(dtype + 1) = DTY(o_dt + 1);
3204 return dtype;
3205}

3207/** \brief Duplicate a dtype array record and its array descriptor, excluding a
3208 dimension.
3209 \param o_dt old array dtype
3210 \param elem_dt element dtype
3211 \param astdim ast of dimension to be excluded
3212 \param after std after which code is produced to create the bounds
3213 descriptor (if dim is not a constant)
3214 */
3215DTYPE
3216reduc_rank_dtype(DTYPE o_dt, DTYPE elem_dt, int astdim, int after)
3217{
3218 DTYPE dtype;
3219 int numdim;
3220 int o_numdim;
3221 int dim;
3222 ADSC *o_ad;
3223 ADSC *ad;
3224 int i, j;
3225
3226 o_ad = AD_DPTR(o_dt);
3227 o_numdim = AD_NUMDIM(o_ad);
3228 numdim = o_numdim - 1;
3229 if (numdim <= 0)
3230 return DTY(o_dt + 1);
3231
3232 dtype = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, elem_dt);
3233 DTY(dtype + 2) = aux.arrdsc_avl;
3234 aux.arrdsc_avl += (_FP + 1) + (_VP * numdim);
3235 NEED(aux.arrdsc_avl, aux.arrdsc_base, int, aux.arrdsc_size,
3236 aux.arrdsc_avl + 240);
3237 o_ad = AD_DPTR(o_dt); /* recreate pointer after possible realloc */
3238 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3239 if (A_ALIASG(astdim) == 0) {
3240 error(422, 3, gbl.lineno, NULL, NULL);
3241 dim = 1;
3242 /* TBD insert code after 'after' to compute bound excluding dim
3243 at run-time */
3244 } else {
3245 /* dim is a constant */
3246
3247 dim = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(astdim)));
3248 if (dim < 1 || dim > o_numdim) {
3249 error(423, 3, gbl.lineno, NULL, NULL);
3250 dim = 1;
3251 }
3252 }
3253 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3254 BZERO(ad, int, (_FP + 1) + _VP * numdim);
3255 j = 0;
3256 for (i = 0; i < o_numdim; i++)
3257 if (i != dim - 1) {
3258 AD_LWBD(ad, j) = AD_LWBD(o_ad, i);
3259 AD_UPBD(ad, j) = AD_UPBD(o_ad, i);
3260 AD_LWAST(ad, j) = AD_LWAST(o_ad, i);
3261 AD_UPAST(ad, j) = AD_UPAST(o_ad, i);
3262 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, j) = AD_EXTNTAST(o_ad, i);
3263 j++;
3264 }
3265 AD_NUMDIM(ad) = numdim;
3266
3267 return dtype;
3268}

3379/** \brief Return true if the data types for two arrays are conformable
3380 (have the same shape). Shape is defined to be the rank and
3381 the extents of each dimension.
3382 */
3383LOGICAL
3384conformable(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
3385{
3386 int ndim;
3387 int i;
3388 int bnd;
3389 INT lb1, lb2;
3390 INT ub1, ub2;
3391 ADSC *ad1, *ad2;
3392
3393 ad1 = AD_DPTR(d1);
3394 ad2 = AD_DPTR(d2);
3395 ndim = AD_NUMDIM(ad1);
3396 if (ndim != AD_NUMDIM(ad2))
3397 return FALSE;
3398
3399 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
3400 bnd = AD_LWAST(ad1, i);
3401 if (bnd) {
3402 bnd = A_ALIASG(bnd);
3403 if (bnd == 0)
3404 continue; /* nonconstant bound => skip this dimension */
3405 lb1 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(bnd));
3406 } else {
3407 lb1 = 1; /* no lower bound => 1 */
3408 }
3409
3410 bnd = AD_UPAST(ad1, i);
3411 if (bnd) {
3412 bnd = A_ALIASG(bnd);
3413 if (bnd == 0)
3414 continue; /* nonconstant bound => skip this dimension */
3415 ub1 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(bnd));
3416 } else {
3417 continue; /* no upper bound => skip this dimension */
3418 }
3419
3420 bnd = AD_LWAST(ad2, i);
3421 if (bnd) {
3422 bnd = A_ALIASG(bnd);
3423 if (bnd == 0)
3424 continue; /* nonconstant bound => skip this dimension */
3425 lb2 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(bnd));
3426 } else {
3427 lb2 = 1; /* no lower bound => 1 */
3428 }
3429
3430 bnd = AD_UPAST(ad2, i);
3431 if (bnd) {
3432 bnd = A_ALIASG(bnd);
3433 if (bnd == 0)
3434 continue; /* nonconstant bound => skip this dimension */
3435 ub2 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(bnd));
3436 } else {
3437 continue; /* no upper bound => skip this dimension */
3438 }
3439
3440 /* upper and lower bounds in this dimension are constants */
3441
3442 if ((ub1 - lb1) != (ub2 - lb2))
3443 return FALSE;
3444 }
3445
3446 return TRUE;
3447}

3604/** \brief For intrinsic types, return same value as the KIND intrinsic */
3605int
3606kind_of(DTYPE d1)
3607{
3608 int ty1;
3609 int k;
3610
3611 ty1 = DTY(d1);
3612 if (ty1 < 0 || ty1 >= TY_MAX)
3613 return 0;
3614 if (!TY_ISBASIC(ty1))
3615 return 0;
3616 switch (ty1) {
3617 case TY_CHAR:
3618 k = 1;
3619 break;
3620 case TY_NCHAR:
3621 k = 2;
3622 break;
3623 case TY_CMPLX:
3624 case TY_DCMPLX:
3625 case TY_QCMPLX:
3626 k = size_of(d1) / 2;
3627 break;
3628 default:
3629 k = size_of(d1);
3630 break;
3631 }
3632 return k;
3633}

3635LOGICAL
3636same_type_different_kind(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
3637{
3638 int ty1, ty2;
3639 ty1 = DTY(d1);
3640 ty2 = DTY(d2);
3641 if (ty1 < 0 || ty2 < 0 || ty1 >= TY_MAX || ty2 >= TY_MAX)
3642 return FALSE;
3643 if (ty_to_base_ty[ty1] == ty_to_base_ty[ty2])
3644 return TRUE;
3645 return FALSE;
3646} /* same_type_different_kind */
3647
3648LOGICAL
3649different_type_same_kind(DTYPE d1, DTYPE d2)
3650{
3651 int ty1, ty2;
3652 int k1, k2;
3653 ty1 = DTY(d1);
3654 ty2 = DTY(d2);
3655 if (ty1 < 0 || ty2 < 0 || ty1 >= TY_MAX || ty2 >= TY_MAX)
3656 return FALSE;
3657 /* at least the TYs must be different */
3658 if (ty1 == ty2)
3659 return FALSE;
3660 k1 = kind_of(d1);
3661 k2 = kind_of(d2);
3662 if (k1 != k2)
3663 return FALSE;
3664 return TRUE;
3665} /* different_type_same_kind */

3720int
3721chk_kind_parm_set_expr(int ast, DTYPE dtype)
3722{
3723 int sptr, newast1, newast2, i, val;
3724
3725 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
3726 case A_INTR:
3727 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
3728 case I_INT1:
3729 case I_INT2:
3730 case I_INT4:
3731 case I_INT8:
3732 case I_INT:
3733 i = A_ARGSG(ast);
3734 newast1 = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(ARGT_ARG(i, 0), dtype);
3735 return newast1 < 0 ? -1 : newast1;
3736 }
3737 break;
3738 case A_CNST:
3739 break;
3740 case A_ID:
3741 if (dtype == 0)
3742 break;
3743 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
3744 if (get_kind_set_parm(sptr, dtype, &val)) {
3745 return mk_cval1(val, DT_INT);
3746 }
3747 val = 0;
3748 i = get_len_set_parm(sptr, dtype, &val);
3749 if (i || val) {
3750 if (val && A_TYPEG(val) == A_ID) {
3751 return ast;
3752 } else if (val) {
3753 return chk_kind_parm_set_expr(val, dtype);
3754 } else {
3755 return mk_cval1(i, DT_INT);
3756 }
3757 } else {
3758 return -1;
3759 }
3760 break;
3761 case A_UNOP:
3762 newast1 = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(A_LOPG(ast), dtype);
3763 if (newast1 < 0)
3764 return -1;
3765 A_LOPP(ast, newast1);
3766 break;
3767 case A_BINOP:
3768 newast1 = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(A_LOPG(ast), dtype);
3769 if (newast1 < 0)
3770 return -1;
3771 newast2 = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(A_ROPG(ast), dtype);
3772 if (newast2 < 0)
3773 return -1;
3774 A_LOPP(ast, newast1);
3775 A_ROPP(ast, newast2);
3776
3777 if (A_TYPEG(newast1) == A_CNST && A_TYPEG(newast2) == A_CNST) {
3778 i = const_fold(A_OPTYPEG(ast), CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(newast1)),
3779 CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(newast2)), A_DTYPEG(ast));
3780 ast = mk_cval1(i, DT_INT);
3781 }
3782 break;
3783 default:
3784 return -1;
3785 }
3786
3787 return ast;
3788}
3789
3790static LOGICAL
3791get_kind_set_parm(int sptr, DTYPE dtype, int *val)
3792{
3793 int mem;
3794
3795 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_DERIVED)
3796 return FALSE;
3797
3798 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
3799 if (PARENTG(mem)) {
3800 if (get_kind_set_parm(sptr, DTYPEG(mem), val)) {
3801 return TRUE;
3802 }
3803 }
3804 if (!LENPARMG(mem) && SETKINDG(mem) && !USEKINDG(mem) && KINDG(mem) &&
3805 strcmp(SYMNAME(mem), SYMNAME(sptr)) == 0) {
3806 *val = KINDG(mem);
3807 return TRUE;
3808 }
3809 }
3810
3811 return FALSE;
3812}
3813
3814static int
3815get_len_set_parm(int sptr, DTYPE dtype, int *val)
3816{
3817 int rslt, mem;
3818
3819 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_DERIVED)
3820 return 0;
3821
3822 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
3823 if (PARENTG(mem)) {
3824 rslt = get_len_set_parm(sptr, DTYPEG(mem), val);
3825 if (rslt)
3826 return rslt;
3827 }
3828 if (LENPARMG(mem) && SETKINDG(mem) && !USEKINDG(mem) && KINDG(mem) &&
3829 strcmp(SYMNAME(mem), SYMNAME(sptr)) == 0) {
3830 *val = LENG(mem);
3831 return KINDG(mem);
3832 }
3833 }
3834
3835 return 0;
3836}

3838/** \brief Compute size and alignment of struct and union types and their
3839 * members.
3840 */
3841void
3842chkstruct(DTYPE dtype)
3843{
3844 int m, m_prev = NOSYM, m_next = NOSYM;
3845 ISZ_T symlk;
3846
3847 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_STRUCT || DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
3848 int offset = 0; /* byte offset from beginning of struct */
3849 int maxa = 0; /* maximum alignment req'd by any member */
3850 int distmem = 0; /* any distributed members? */
3851 int ptrmem = 0; /* any pointer members? */
3852
3853 for (m = DTY(dtype + 1); m != NOSYM; m_prev = m, m = symlk) {
3854 int oldoffset, a;
3855 symlk = SYMLKG(m);
3856 m_next = symlk;
3857 if (DTYPEG(m) == DT_NONE) {
3858 continue; /* Occurs w/ empty typedef */
3859 }
3860 if (is_tbp_or_final(m)) {
3861 /* skip tbp */
3862 continue;
3863 }
3864 a = alignment_of_var(m);
3865 offset = ALIGN(offset, a);
3866 oldoffset = offset;
3867 ADDRESSP(m, offset);
3868 if (DTY(DTYPEG(m)) == TY_ARRAY
3869 && !MIDNUMG(m) && !ADJARRG(m) && !POINTERG(m)
3870 && !RUNTIMEG(m)) {
3871 if (extent_of(DTYPEG(m)) != 0)
3872 offset += size_of_var(m);
3873 } else
3874 offset += size_of_var(m);
3875/* if this is a pointer member, and the next member
3876 * is the actual pointer, let the pointer/offset/descriptor
3877 * overlap */
3878 if ((POINTERG(m) || ALLOCG(m) || ADJARRG(m) || RUNTIMEG(m)) &&
3879 MIDNUMG(m) == symlk)
3880 offset = oldoffset;
3881 if (POINTERG(m))
3882 ptrmem = 1;
3883 if (a > maxa)
3884 maxa = a;
3885 PSMEMP(m, m);
3886 if (ALIGNG(m) || DISTG(m)) {
3887 distmem = 1;
3888 } else {
3889 DTYPE d = DTYPEG(m);
3890 if (DTY(d) == TY_DERIVED) {
3891 int tag = DTY(d + 3);
3892 if (tag) {
3893 if (DISTMEMG(tag))
3894 distmem = 1;
3895 if (POINTERG(tag))
3896 ptrmem = 1;
3897 }
3898 }
3899 }
3900 }
3901 /* compute final size and alignment of struct: */
3902
3903 DTY(dtype + 2) = ALIGN(offset, maxa);
3904 if (distmem && DTY(dtype + 3)) {
3905 DISTMEMP(DTY(dtype + 3), 1);
3906 }
3907 DTY(dtype + 4) = maxa;
3908 if (ptrmem && DTY(dtype + 3)) {
3909 POINTERP(DTY(dtype + 3), 1);
3910 }
3911 } else {
3912 /*
3913 * Size and alignment of a union are the maximum of the sizes and
3914 * alignments of its members:
3915 */
3916 int maxa = 0;
3917 ISZ_T size = 1;
3918 assert(DTY(dtype) == TY_UNION && DTY(dtype + 1), "chkstruct:bad dt", dtype,
3919 3);
3920 for (m = DTY(dtype + 1); m != NOSYM; m_prev = m, m = symlk) {
3921 symlk = SYMLKG(m);
3922 m_next = symlk;
3923 ISZ_T s = size_of_var(m);
3924 int a = alignment_of_var(m);
3925 if (s > size)
3926 size = s;
3927 if (a > maxa)
3928 maxa = a;
3929 }
3930 DTY(dtype + 2) = ALIGN(size, maxa);
3931 DTY(dtype + 4) = maxa;
3932 }
3933}

3965static DTYPE
3966get_iso_derivedtype(DTYPE d_dtype)
3967{
3968 int check_mod;
3969 DTYPE dtype = d_dtype;
3970 int mod = lookupsymbol("iso_c_binding");
3971
3972 if (mod == 0)
3973 return 0;
3974
3975 /* yes to array of c_ptrs */
3976 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
3977 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
3978
3979 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED && DTY(dtype + 3))
3980 check_mod = DTY(dtype + 3); /* tag */
3981 else
3982 check_mod = 0;
3983
3984 if (gbl.internal > 1) {
3985 /* If a contained subprogram has USEd iso_c_binding, a temporary,
3986 * incomplete symbol table entry may have been generated. Find the
3987 * correct (complete) one.
3988 */
3989 for (; mod && STYPEG(mod) != ST_MODULE; mod = HASHLKG(mod)) {
3990 if (strcmp(SYMNAME(mod), "iso_c_binding") == 0 &&
3991 STYPEG(mod) == ST_MODULE) {
3992 break;
3993 }
3994 }
3995 }
3996
3997 if (check_mod <= 0 || ENCLFUNCG(check_mod) <= 0)
3998 return 0;
3999
4000 if (ENCLFUNCG(check_mod) == mod) {
4001 ISOCTYPEP(check_mod, 1);
4002 return dtype;
4003 }
4004
4005 return 0;
4006}

4042DTYPE
4043get_iso_ptrtype(const char *name)
4044{
4045 int s, sptr;
4046 int mod;
4047 int check_mod;
4048
4049 mod = lookupsymbol("iso_c_binding");
4050 if (mod == 0)
4051 return 0;
4052
4053 s = getsymbol(name);
4054 for (sptr = first_hash(s); sptr; sptr = HASHLKG(sptr)) {
4055 if (NMPTRG(sptr) != NMPTRG(s))
4056 continue;
4057 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_TYPEDEF)
4058 continue;
4059 check_mod = DTY(DTYPEG(sptr) + 3); /* tag */
4060 if ((check_mod <= 0) || (ENCLFUNCG(check_mod) <= 0))
4061 continue;

4075/* FIXME: create common utility that can be shared with sem_strcmp */
4076/** \brief Compare \a str and \a pattern like strcmp() but ignoring the case of
4077 str.
4078 \a pattern is all lower case.
4079 */
4080static int
4081ic_strcmp(const char *str, const char *pattern)
4082{
4083 const char *p1, *p2;
4084 int ch;
4085
4086 p1 = str;
4087 p2 = pattern;
4088 do {
4089 ch = *p1;
4090 if (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z')
4091 ch += ('a' - 'A'); /* to lower case */
4092 if (ch != *p2)
4093 return (ch - *p2);
4094 if (ch == '\0')
4095 return 0;
4096 p1++;
4097 p2++;
4098 } while (1);
4099}

4251{
4252 SPTR tag;
4253 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
4254 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
4255 tag = get_struct_tag_sptr(dtype);
4256 if (tag > NOSYM) {
4257 SPTR member;
4258 if (BASETYPEG(tag) > DT_NONE)
4259 return FALSE; /* the BASETYPE here means the original p.d.t. */
4260 for (member = get_struct_members(dtype);
4261 member > NOSYM; member = SYMLKG(member)) {

4263 return TRUE;
4264 }
4265 }
4266 return FALSE;
4267}
